('1', 'one', '一', '<img src=\"E4B880.png\" />', 'One', '1', '1', 'One down, 2041 to go. ;).', '1', '5', 'イチ、イツ', 'ひと-、ひと.つ', NULL, NULL),
('10', 'ten', '十', '<img src=\"E58D81.png\" />', 'ten, needle', '2', '1', 'Two needles crossing marks the spot, or you can use the Roman character for ten (rotated 45 degrees).', '1', '5', 'ジュウ、ジッ、ジュッ', 'とお、と', NULL, NULL),
('100', 'cavity', '孔', '<img src=\"E5AD94.png\" />', 'cavity, child, fishhook', '4', '6', 'The child´s arms flailed around at the sight of the hooked tool the dentist was going to use to fill his cavity.', 'JH', '1', 'コウ', 'あな', NULL, NULL),
('1000', 'sort', '類', '<img src=\"E9A19E.png\" />', 'sort, rice, large, St. Bernard, head, page, one, ceiling, drop, shellfish, clam, oyster, eye, animal legs, eight', '18', '26', 'Note this character means sort in the sense of what kind, I believe a better keyword would be \"variety\" and this character does appear in some dictionaries with the primary meaning as variety, my story: I´m in a Chinese restaurant and the waiter says \"What sort of rice would you like with your dog head?\".', '4', '3', 'ルイ', 'たぐ.い', NULL, NULL),
('1001', 'lacquer', '漆', '<img src=\"E6BC86.png\" />', 'lacquer, water, water droplets, water pistol, tree, wood, umbrella, grains of rice', '14', '26', 'LACQUER is a type of WATERY type of liquid used to protect items made from TREES, sort of an UMBRELLA of protection. So protective, you can carry around RICE in the LACQUERED, WOODEN product.', 'JH', '1', 'シツ', 'うるし', NULL, NULL),
('1002', 'knee', '膝', '<img src=\"E8869D.png\" />', 'knee, moon, month, flesh, part of the body, tree, wood, umbrella, grains of rice', '13', '26', 'Before lacquer (#932) was made with water, it was made by draining this body part of fluid: the knee!', 'JH', '', 'シツ', 'ひざ', NULL, NULL),
('1003', 'Esq.', '様', '<img src=\"E6A798.png\" />', 'Esq., tree, wood, sheep, grains of rice', '14', '26', 'Here we have the requirements to be counted among the ranks of the noble Esq. You must posses a forested estate, herds of sheep, and granary full of grains of rice.', '3', '3', 'ヨウ、ショウ', 'さま、さん', NULL, NULL),
('1004', 'request', '求', '<img src=\"E6B182.png\" />', 'request, arrow, grains of rice', '7', '26', 'Enemy: \"Any final requests?\" // MacGyver: \"Just an arrowhead and some grains of rice.\" (MacGyver then throws the grains of rice at the enemy and uses the arrowhead to cut his hands free from the rope.).', '4', '3', 'キュウ、グ', 'もと.める', NULL, NULL),
('1005', 'ball', '球', '<img src=\"E79083.png\" />', 'ball, king, jewel, ball, request, arrow, grains of rice', '11', '26', 'Someone files a request to see the family jewels and, to their surprise, you show them your balls!', '3', '3', 'キュウ', 'たま', NULL, NULL),
('1006', 'salvation', '救', '<img src=\"E69591.png\" />', 'salvation, request, arrow, grains of rice, taskmaster', '11', '26', 'Like in the biblical sense, someone looks skyward and makes a request for salvation from this horrible taskmaster...', '4', '1', 'キュウ', 'すく.う', NULL, NULL),
('1007', 'bamboo', '竹', '<img src=\"E7ABB9.png\" />', 'bamboo', '6', '26', 'Pandas like to eat bamboo. I´m using panda as the primitive name when it fits the story. ^__^.', '1', '2', 'チク', 'たけ', NULL, NULL),
('1008', 'laugh', '笑', '<img src=\"E7AC91.png\" />', 'laugh, bamboo, heavens', '10', '26', 'When the people tried to build a tower of bamboo to reach the heavens, the gods just laughed and laughed.', '4', '3', 'ショウ', 'わら.う、え.む', NULL, NULL),
('1009', 'bamboo hat', '笠', '<img src=\"E7ACA0.png\" />', 'bamboo hat, bamboo, vase, stand up', '11', '26', 'The bamboo vase was beautifully crafted, but the tourist didn´t know what it was and wore it as a little bamboo hat.', 'Nam', '', 'リュウ', 'かさ', NULL, NULL),
('101', 'complete', '了', '<img src=\"E4BA86.png\" />', 'complete, child with arms wrapped up', '2', '6', 'The experiment was a complete failure! The child was made without any arms!', 'JH', '2', 'リョウ', '', NULL, NULL),
('1010', 'bamboo grass', '笹', '<img src=\"E7ACB9.png\" />', 'bamboo grass, bamboo, generation', '11', '26', 'The bamboo generation smokes bamboo grass.', 'Nam', '1', '', 'ささ', NULL, NULL),
('1011', 'stationery', '箋・䇳', '<img src=\"E7AE8B.png\" />', 'stationery, bamboo, float, fiesta, float*, fiesta2', '12', '26', 'Note: the spelling should be stationery (= paper, office supplies), not stationary (= not moving). The error is in the original book.', 'JH', '', 'セン', 'ふだ', NULL, NULL),
('1012', 'muscle', '筋', '<img src=\"E7AD8B.png\" />', 'muscle, bamboo, moon, month, flesh, part of the body, power, muscle, arnold', '12', '26', 'Muscle is part of the body that gives strength, and can be both supple and tense like the bamboo.', '6', '1', 'キン', 'すじ', NULL, NULL),
('1013', 'box', '箱', '<img src=\"E7AEB1.png\" />', 'box , bamboo, inter, Inter Milan, tree, wood, eye', '15', '26', 'The best kind of BOX is made from BAMBOO sticks that are INTER-laced to make it air tight. Just picture such a box and you´ve mastered this kanji.', '3', '3', 'ソウ', 'はこ', NULL, NULL),
('1014', 'writing brush', '筆', '<img src=\"E7AD86.png\" />', 'writing brush, bamboo, brush', '12', '26', 'Bamboo is the best material from which to make a brush if you want it to be a writing brush.', '3', '2', 'ヒツ', 'ふで', NULL, NULL),
('1015', 'cylinder', '筒', '<img src=\"E7AD92.png\" />', 'cylinder, bamboo, same, monks, hood, one, mouth', '12', '26', 'Seriously, all BAMBOO sticks look the SAME, just long CYLINDERS. Should the story be more complicated?', 'JH', '2', 'トウ', 'つつ', NULL, NULL),
('1016', 'etc.', '等', '<img src=\"E7AD89.png\" />', 'etc., bamboo, Buddhist temple, soil, dirt, ground, glue', '12', '26', 'The Bamboo Buddhist Temple has bamboo buddhas, bamboo buildings, bamboo benches, bamboo beds, bamboo bowls, etc. etc. etc.', '3', '3', 'トウ', 'ひと.しい、など、-ら', NULL, NULL),
('1017', 'calculate', '算', '<img src=\"E7AE97.png\" />', 'calculate, bamboo, eye, two hands', '14', '26', 'Before the time of digital calculators, people used old school calculators made of bamboo (abacus). It´s not as easy as a calculator, but you don´t need any batteries either. All you need are your eyes and your two hands.', '2', '2', 'サン', 'そろ', NULL, NULL),
('1018', 'solution', '答', '<img src=\"E7AD94.png\" />', 'solution, bamboo, fit, meeting, umbrella, one, mouth', '12', '26', 'The solution to this puzzle is, like the match stick game, to make the bamboo pieces fit together.', '2', '4', 'トウ', 'こた.える、こた.え', NULL, NULL),
('1019', 'scheme', '策', '<img src=\"E7AD96.png\" />', 'scheme, bamboo, tree, wood, belt', '12', '26', '(Elaboration of jameserb´s story:) A clever scheme from Wile E Coyote -- he ties one of those rubber belts to some trees and uses it to launch a bamboo spear at the roadrunner...', '6', '1', 'サク', '', NULL, NULL),
('102', 'woman', '女', '<img src=\"E5A5B3.png\" />', 'woman', '3', '6', 'To remember the order of strokes, remember a female ninja is called a \"kunoichi\". That is, く(hiragana) ノ(katakana) 一(kanji, ichi=one).', '1', '5', 'ジョ、ニョ、ニョウ', 'おんな、め', NULL, NULL),
('1020', 'register', '簿', '<img src=\"E7B0BF.png\" />', 'register, bamboo, water, water droplets, water pistol, acupuncturist, specialty, drop, ten, needle, rice field, brains, glue', '19', '26', 'Note : the keyword is not a verb, think of a record book. This acupuncturist who uses bamboo in place of flowers to dilute water into his patients (see frame 227), managed somehow to appear on the register of acupuncturists. Chances are, he won´t stay on the register for long. My image is close to that of gorgon´s story.', 'JH', '1', 'ボ', '', NULL, NULL),
('1021', 'fabricate', '築', '<img src=\"E7AF89.png\" />', 'fabricate, bamboo, barge, craft, mediocre, wind, drop, tree, wood', '16', '26', 'Bamboo crafting is a mediocre substitute for wood when you are building or fabricating a house. While it may look good and might attract a chick (ちく) or two, the kids´ll (きず) just tear it to pieces as its not sturdy enough.', '5', '2', 'チク', 'きず.く', NULL, NULL),
('1022', 'basket', '篭・籠', '<img src=\"E7AFAD.png\" />', 'cage, bamboo, dragon, vase, stand up, eel, sun, day', '16', '26', 'The only cage that can keep a dragon is made of bamboo.', 'JH', '', 'ロウ、ル', 'かご、こ.める、こも.る、こ.む', NULL, NULL),
('1023', 'person', '人', '<img src=\"E4BABA.png\" />', 'person', '2', '27', 'Behold Mister T (of \"A-Team\" fame)! I chose Mr.T because he´s sure to make amusing stories. He is a very versatile character since he´s both the big, tough guy and the “moralistic” person, telling kids not “to do drugs or alcohol”. He is easy to imagine, the heavy gold chains are probably the most prominent feature of the character. And last but not least you can always pepper your story with the famous line “I pity da foo!” * Fittingly, on the left side of the kanji, it looks like a “T”.', '1', '5', 'ジン、ニン', 'ひと、-り、-と', NULL, NULL),
('1024', 'assistant', '佐', '<img src=\"E4BD90.png\" />', 'assistant, person, left, by one’s side, craft', '7', '27', 'Mr T´s assistant is on his left. Why? Because Mr T has this bad habit of suddenly extending his right arm (what with all the boxing that he did), and his assistant got inadvertently punched in the face more than once (ouch). So now his assistant is always to his left side, much safer - \"Stay on my left, foo!\".', 'JH', '1', 'サ', '', NULL, NULL),
('1025', 'partner', '侶', '<img src=\"E4BEB6.png\" />', 'partner, person, spine, mouth, drop, mouth, mouth2', '9', '27', 'Mr. T don´t take a partner, especially one with no spine. \"I pity da foo got no spine\", he says.', 'JH', '', 'リョ、ロ', 'とも', NULL, NULL),
('1026', 'however', '但', '<img src=\"E4BD86.png\" />', 'however, person, nightbreak, sun, day, one, floor', '7', '27', 'However drunk Mr T is when he comes back to his place, he always get up at nightbreak. “I pity da foo who gets up after nightbreak !”, says Mr. T.', 'JH', '1', 'タン', 'ただ.し', NULL, NULL),
('1027', 'dwell', '住', '<img src=\"E4BD8F.png\" />', 'dwell, person, candlestick, lord, drop, king, jewel, ball', '7', '27', 'When Mr T shows people round his dwelling he takes a big candlestick (with a candle in it!) so that the light shows off his collection of bling bling jewellery.', '3', '4', 'ジュウ、ヂュウ、チュウ', 'す.む、す.まう、-ず.まい', NULL, NULL),
('1028', 'rank', '位', '<img src=\"E4BD8D.png\" />', 'rank, person, vase, stand up', '7', '27', 'Mr T ranks first position in the stand-up competition (doing knee flexions). Just picture him doing hundreds of these while the rest of the participants are already completely exhausted after a mere hundred.', '4', '3', 'イ', 'くらい、ぐらい', NULL, NULL),
('1029', 'go-between', '仲', '<img src=\"E4BBB2.png\" />', 'go-between, person, in, stick, mouth', '6', '27', 'When negotiating a hostage situation, Mr. T acted as the go-between, or person in the middle, for law enforcement and the terrorist.', '4', '2', 'チュウ', 'なか', NULL, NULL),
('103', 'fond', '好', '<img src=\"E5A5BD.png\" />', 'fond, woman, child', '6', '6', 'A woman is fond of her child.', '4', '3', 'コウ', 'この.む、す.く、よ.い、い.い', NULL, NULL),
('1030', 'body', '体', '<img src=\"E4BD93.png\" />', 'body, person, origin, book, tree, wood, one', '7', '27', 'Mister T works out his body (body-building), using two piles of books (i.e. an exercise that can be done at home with two chairs, similar to push-ups but working mostly the shoulders, trapezius and triceps).', '2', '4', 'タイ、テイ', 'からだ、かたち', NULL, NULL),
('1031', 'remote', '悠', '<img src=\"E682A0.png\" />', 'permanence, remote, person, stick, fred astaire, taskmaster, heart', '11', '27', 'Mr. T ventured out into a remote area to visit with his wise, old taskmaster who must use a walking stick to get around and originally gave Mr. T the heart to fight crime for the good of the community.', 'JH', '1', 'ユウ', '', NULL, NULL),
('1032', 'affair', '件', '<img src=\"E4BBB6.png\" />', 'affair, person, cow', '6', '27', 'Note: this kanji refers to event or case. Current Affair headline: Mr. T has affair with cow. \"It´s only animal ´man´ enough for me\".', '5', '3', 'ケン', 'くだん', NULL, NULL),
('1033', 'attend', '仕', '<img src=\"E4BB95.png\" />', 'attend, person, samurai', '5', '27', 'Back in the day, a person who stands beside a samurai is usually attending to them or working for them.', '3', '4', 'シ、ジ', 'つか.える', NULL, NULL),
('1034', 'other', '他', '<img src=\"E4BB96.png\" />', 'other, person, scorpion', '5', '27', 'Old latin saying: homo hominis scorpio (people are scorpions to other people).', '3', '3', 'タ', 'ほか', NULL, NULL),
('1035', 'prostrated', '伏', '<img src=\"E4BC8F.png\" />', 'prostrated, person, chihuahua, dog, large, drop', '6', '27', 'Don´t need a silly story for this one: prostration is when a person puts themselves in a low position like a dog, as an extreme gesture of humility.', 'JH', '1', 'フク', 'ふ.せる、ふ.す', NULL, NULL),
('1036', 'transmit', '伝', '<img src=\"E4BC9D.png\" />', 'transmit, person, rising cloud, two, elbow, wall', '6', '27', 'Mister T transmits a message with rising clouds (smoke) signals, to a nearby American Indian tribe. The smoke signals spell : \"I p-i-t-y y-o-u f-o-o !\".', '4', '3', 'デン、テン', 'つた.わる、つた.える、つた.う、つだ.う、-づた.い、つて', NULL, NULL),
('1037', 'Buddha', '仏', '<img src=\"E4BB8F.png\" />', 'buddha, person, elbow', '4', '27', 'Mr. T says, \"I ain´t afraid o´ no foo! I´ll give anyone an elbow to the face, I don´t care if it´s Buddha himself!\".', '5', '2', 'ブツ、フツ', 'ほとけ', NULL, NULL),
('1038', 'rest', '休', '<img src=\"E4BC91.png\" />', 'rest, person, tree, wood', '6', '27', 'Mr T resting by a tree.', '1', '5', 'キュウ', 'やす.む、やす.まる、やす.める', NULL, NULL),
('1039', 'provisional', '仮', '<img src=\"E4BBAE.png\" />', 'sham, provisional, person, anti-, demonstration, cliff, crotch', '6', '27', 'Mr. T was offered a job in the Iraq Provisional Authority, but he turned it down, because he´s anti-war. \"I pity da fool thinks this sand pit worth invadin´ when our schools be in such sad shape!\".', '5', '1', 'カ、ケ', 'かり、かり-', NULL, NULL),
('104', 'likeness', '如', '<img src=\"E5A682.png\" />', 'likeness, woman, mouth', '6', '6', 'Women share a common likeness. Their mouths are always open, whining about this and that.', 'JH', '1', 'ジョ、ニョ', 'ごと.し', NULL, NULL),
('1040', 'performing artist', '伎', '<img src=\"E4BC8E.png\" />', 'performing artist, person, branch, ten, needle, crotch', '6', '27', 'Mr T is dancing and singing and all that, but he´s doing it on a branch. All that talent and can still still keep his balance? That´s a real performing artist.', 'JH', '1', 'ギ、キ', 'わざ、わざおぎ', NULL, NULL),
('1041', 'chief', '伯', '<img src=\"E4BCAF.png\" />', 'chief, person, white, dove', '7', '27', 'If Mr T was white I am sure he would have been commander in chief of the USA, he just the sort of clown Americans love to vote for. (NB: I tried with the indian chief motif but kept adding feathers by mistake).', 'JH', '1', 'ハク', '', NULL, NULL),
('1042', 'vulgar', '俗', '<img src=\"E4BF97.png\" />', 'vulgar, person, valley, eight, umbrella, mouth', '9', '27', 'Mr. T says, \"Don´t be like them valley girls, always speaking vulgar language and acting all vulgar! They ain´t nothing but foos!\".', 'JH', '1', 'ゾク', '', NULL, NULL),
('1043', 'faith', '信', '<img src=\"E4BFA1.png\" />', 'faith, person, say, words, keitai, mouth', '9', '27', 'Mr. T has faith in the Word of God. (Image: Mr. T kneeling and prayering in front of a bible. \"Pity me, fool.\").', '4', '3', 'シン', '', NULL, NULL),
('1044', 'excellent', '佳', '<img src=\"E4BDB3.png\" />', 'excellent, person, ivy, square jewel, soil, dirt, ground, soil2, dirt2, ground2', '8', '27', 'Mr T wants to go to an excellent school, so he enrolls in Harvard, an ivy-league school.', 'JH', '1', 'カ', '', NULL, NULL),
('1045', 'reliant', '依', '<img src=\"E4BE9D.png\" />', 'reliant, person, cloth, clothes, clothing, garment', '8', '27', 'Mr T is reliant (depends on) on his garment (the gold chains).', 'JH', '2', 'イ、エ', 'よ.る', NULL, NULL),
('1046', 'example', '例', '<img src=\"E4BE8B.png\" />', 'example, person, file, bones, one, ceiling, evening, sword, sabre, saber', '8', '27', 'Mr T shows the example to the kids, and stays in the file (at supermarket, ...). “I pity da foo who does not follow my example !”.', '4', '3', 'レイ', 'たと.える', NULL, NULL),
('1047', 'individual', '個', '<img src=\"E5808B.png\" />', 'individual, person, harden, pent in, old, tombstone, gravestone, church, ten, needle, mouth', '10', '27', 'This keyword gave me trouble, I could write the kanji from memory but could not remember the keyword the other way around. In such case the dictionary definition can be helpful : \"Middle English, single, indivisible\". Here we have Mr. T. who is so hardened (all the body workout he´s had) that he became in-dividual, that is, in-divisible. \"I pity da foo who can be divided into smaller units.\".', '5', '2', 'コ、カ', '', NULL, NULL),
('1048', 'healthy', '健', '<img src=\"E581A5.png\" />', 'healthy, person, build, brush, stretch', '11', '27', 'Mr. T in a public service announcement yells, \"I´m healthy because every day I build a food pyramid, foo!\".', '4', '1', 'ケン', 'すこ.やか', NULL, NULL),
('1049', 'side', '側', '<img src=\"E581B4.png\" />', 'side, person, rule, shellfish, clam, oyster, eye, animal legs, eight, sword, sabre, saber', '11', '27', 'Mr. T rulezzz! I am on his side!', '4', '3', 'ソク', 'かわ、がわ、そば', NULL, NULL),
('105', 'mama', '母', '<img src=\"E6AF8D.png\" />', 'mama, mother, breasts', '5', '6', 'The two breasts of a momma who breastfeeds.', '2', '5', 'ボ', 'はは、も', NULL, NULL),
('1050', 'waiter', '侍', '<img src=\"E4BE8D.png\" />', 'waiter, person, Buddhist temple, soil, dirt, ground, glue', '8', '27', 'Mr. T infiltrates the secret samurai Buddhist temple as a waiter with a tray of green tea. (Careful: attend (#960)).', 'JH', '1', 'ジ、シ', 'さむらい、はべ.る', NULL, NULL),
('1051', 'halt', '停', '<img src=\"E5819C.png\" />', 'halt, person, pavilion, tall, top hat, mouth, crown, street, nail, spike', '11', '27', 'Halt fool - Mr T acting as a bouncer at the pavillion.', '4', '2', 'テイ', 'と.める、と.まる', NULL, NULL),
('1052', 'price', '値', '<img src=\"E580A4.png\" />', 'price, person, straightaway, ten, needle, eye, fishhook', '10', '27', 'Mr. T (person) tells the used car salesman to tell him the real price straight away, and when he doesn´t he throws him through the windshield.', '6', '3', 'チ', 'ね、あたい', NULL, NULL),
('1053', 'emulate', '倣', '<img src=\"E580A3.png\" />', 'emulate, person, set free, compass, direction, taskmaster', '10', '27', 'Mr T downloads an emulator so that he can play his favorite game, Pokemon. He plays for a different reason, though - he hates to see them poor little foos in the ball so he spends his entire time setting them free.', 'JH', '1', 'ホウ', 'なら.う', NULL, NULL),
('1054', 'arrogance', '傲', '<img src=\"E582B2.png\" />', '', '13', '27', 'He showed his arrogance as he poured dirt on those who tried to emulate him.', 'JH', '', 'ゴウ', 'あなど.る、 おご.る', NULL, NULL),
('1055', 'overthrow', '倒', '<img src=\"E58092.png\" />', 'overthrow, person, arrival, climax, wall, one, ceiling, elbow, soil, dirt, ground, sword, sabre, saber', '10', '27', 'The A-Team are planning to overthrow the government. However, they can´t do a damn thing until Mr T arrives.', 'JH', '3', 'トウ', 'たお.れる、-だお.れ、たお.す', NULL, NULL),
('1056', 'spy', '偵', '<img src=\"E581B5.png\" />', 'spy, person, upright, magic wand, augury, shellfish, clam, oyster, eye, animal legs, eight', '11', '27', 'Mr. T is a terrible spy. He walks around upright. \"Why should I hide?! I´ve got nothing to be ashamed of!\".', 'JH', '1', 'テイ', '', NULL, NULL),
('1057', 'Buddhist priest', '僧', '<img src=\"E583A7.png\" />', 'buddhist priest, person, increase, formerly, horns, rice field, brains, sun, day', '13', '27', 'While a waiter at the Buddhist temple (see FRAME 976), Mr T increases in wisdom and becomes a Buddhist priest.', 'JH', '1', 'ソウ', '', NULL, NULL),
('1058', 'hundred million', '億', '<img src=\"E58484.png\" />', 'hundred million, person, idea, sound, vase, stand up, sun, day, heart', '15', '27', 'Mr. T has an clear idea of what he would do if he ever got hundred million dollar. (I guess it would be a enormous gold chain !).', '4', '2', 'オク', '', NULL, NULL),
('1059', 'ceremony', '儀', '<img src=\"E58480.png\" />', 'ceremony, person, righteousness, sheep, ego, hand, fiesta', '15', '27', 'Mr. T is the master of ceremonies because he is a righteous dude.', 'JH', '1', 'ギ', '', NULL, NULL),
('106', 'pierce', '貫', '<img src=\"E8B2AB.png\" />', 'pierce, mama, mother, breasts, oyster, shellfish, clam, oyster, eye, animal legs, eight', '11', '6', 'Ariel the Little Mermaid´s clamshell bra was held to her breasts by piercings.', 'JH', '1', 'カン', 'つらぬ.く、ぬ.く、ぬき', NULL, NULL),
('1060', 'reparation', '償', '<img src=\"E5849F.png\" />', 'reparation, person, prize, outhouse, small, little, crown, mouth, shellfish, clam, oyster, eye, animal legs, eight', '17', '27', 'Mr. T says, \"This ain´t no prize, foo! This is reparations for slavery!\".', 'JH', '1', 'ショウ', 'つぐな.う', NULL, NULL),
('1061', 'hermit', '仙', '<img src=\"E4BB99.png\" />', 'hermit, person, mountain', '5', '27', 'A HERMIT is a PERSON who lives in the MOUNTAINS.', 'JH', '1', 'セン、セント', '', NULL, NULL),
('1062', 'sponsor', '催', '<img src=\"E582AC.png\" />', 'sponsor, person, mountain, turkey', '13', '27', 'And now a word from our sponsor. We see Mr. T, doing a sort of George Foreman thing, grilling Mountain Turkeys. \"I pity da foo who don´t have a Mr. T grill!\".', 'JH', '1', 'サイ', 'もよう.す、もよお.す', NULL, NULL),
('1063', 'humanity', '仁', '<img src=\"E4BB81.png\" />', 'humanity, person, two', '4', '27', 'The beginning of humanity required at least TWO people. Mr. T and Mrs. T!', '6', '1', 'ジン、ニ、ニン', '', NULL, NULL),
('1064', 'scorn', '侮', '<img src=\"E4BEAE.png\" />', 'scorn, person, every, reclining, lying down, mother, breasts', '8', '27', 'Mr. T has scorn for every fool.', 'JH', '1', 'ブ', 'あなど.る、あなず.る', NULL, NULL),
