('1150', 'printing', '刷', '<img src=\"E588B7.png\" />', 'printing, flag, towel, sword, sabre, saber', '8', '29', 'We printed a japanese flag on his white towel by stabbing him with a saber while he was wearing it.', '4', '2', 'サツ', 'す.る、-ず.り、-ずり、は.く', NULL, NULL),
('1151', 'shaku', '尺', '<img src=\"E5B0BA.png\" />', 'shaku, flag, stick', '4', '29', 'Slang for blowjob and that´s priceless for stories...but also the character looks like the letter R which I think of as standing for RULER (12 inches) other meanings include: rule, measure, length.', '6', '1', 'シャク', '', NULL, NULL),
('1152', 'exhaust', '尽', '<img src=\"E5B0BD.png\" />', 'exhaust, shaku-hachi, flag, stick, ice', '6', '29', 'A women is so exhausted by her \"shakuhachi\" that see needs to ice her jaw.', 'JH', '1', 'ジン、サン', 'つ.くす、-つ.くす、-づ.くし、-つ.く、-づ.く、-ず.く、つ.きる、つ.かす、さかづき、ことごと.く、つか、つき', NULL, NULL),
('1153', 'swamp', '沢', '<img src=\"E6B2A2.png\" />', 'swamp, water, water droplets, water pistol, shaku-hachi, flag, stick', '7', '29', 'You´re hiding from the enemy underwater in a swamp. To breathe, you have your shakuhachi flute poking up through the surface of the water.', 'JH', '1', 'タク', 'さわ、うるお.い、うるお.す、つや', NULL, NULL),
('1154', 'translate', '訳', '<img src=\"E8A8B3.png\" />', 'translate, say, words, keitai, mouth, shaku-hachi, flag, stick', '11', '29', 'You cannot pretend to translate into words the melody of the shakuhachi!', '6', '1', 'ヤク', 'わけ', NULL, NULL),
('1155', 'choose', '択', '<img src=\"E68A9E.png\" />', 'choose, finger, fingers, shaku-hachi, flag, stick', '7', '29', 'Hand job or \"shakuhachi\", choose.', 'JH', '1', 'タク', 'えら.ぶ', NULL, NULL),
('1156', 'daytime', '昼', '<img src=\"E698BC.png\" />', 'daytime, shaku-hachi, flag, stick, nightbreak, sun, day, one, floor', '9', '29', 'Roosters in Japan are very civilised, they play the shakuhachi at nightbreak to signify the beginning of daytime.', '2', '4', 'チュウ', 'ひる', NULL, NULL),
('1157', 'door', '戸', '<img src=\"E688B8.png\" />', 'door, one, flag', '4', '29', 'Traditional Japanese storefront doors have several flags, known as \"noren,\" hanging down from a curtain rod in front of them. I see this as a pseudo-pictograph, and use the horizontal line across the top to represent the curtain rod, since noren don´t usually hang from the ceiling.', '2', '2', 'コ', 'と', NULL, NULL),
('1158', 'shoulder', '肩', '<img src=\"E882A9.png\" />', 'shoulder, door, one, ceiling, flag, moon, month, flesh, part of the body', '8', '29', 'The shoulder is the best part of the body to bash a door open with (Don´t ever try this. Use your foot).', 'JH', '2', 'ケン', 'かた', NULL, NULL),
('1159', 'tassel', '房', '<img src=\"E688BF.png\" />', 'tassel, door, one, ceiling, flag, compass, direction', '8', '29', 'Explanation here: http://forum.koohii.com/viewtopic.php?pid=14684#p14684.', 'JH', '1', 'ボウ', 'ふさ', NULL, NULL),
('116', 'outside', '外', '<img src=\"E5A496.png\" />', 'outside, evening, magic wand, augury', '5', '7', 'A young magician likes to practice outside in the evening with his magic wand (as opposed to the old magician who wakes early to practice with his wand in eminent (#51)).', '2', '5', 'ガイ、ゲ', 'そと、ほか、はず.す、はず.れる、と-', NULL, NULL),
('1160', 'fan', '扇', '<img src=\"E68987.png\" />', 'fan, door, one, ceiling, flag, feathers, wings', '10', '29', 'It´s insanely hot today! I´m standing in the doorway, fanning myself with feathers.', 'JH', '1', 'セン', 'おうぎ', NULL, NULL),
('1161', 'hearth', '炉', '<img src=\"E78289.png\" />', 'hearth-fire, door, one, ceiling, flag', '8', '29', 'This hearth is equipped with a fire-proof door. On the kanji you can see somewhat pictographically the fire-proof door keeping the fire behind, and nothing comes under the door primitive, where you would have expected to see another primitive.', 'JH', '1', 'ロ', 'いろり', NULL, NULL),
('1162', 're-', '戻', '<img src=\"E688BB.png\" />', 're-, door, one, ceiling, flag, large, St. Bernard', '7', '29', 'The St. Bernard dog whining at the door of his master’s house in order to re-enter / re-turn inside.', 'JH', '3', 'レイ', 'もど.す、もど.る', NULL, NULL),
('1163', 'tears', '涙', '<img src=\"E6B699.png\" />', 'tears, water, water droplets, water pistol, re-, door, one, ceiling, flag, large, St. Bernard', '10', '29', 'I see the story of Hachiko: the faithfull dog who still waited for his master to return long after he had died. Brings a tear to the eye.', 'JH', '2', 'ルイ、レイ', 'なみだ', NULL, NULL),
('1164', 'employ', '雇', '<img src=\"E99B87.png\" />', 'employ, door, one, ceiling, flag, turkey', '12', '29', 'Our company has no standards. We´ll employ any turkey who walks in the door.', 'JH', '2', 'コ', 'やと.う', NULL, NULL),
('1165', 'look back', '顧', '<img src=\"E9A1A7.png\" />', 'look back, employ, door, one, ceiling, flag, turkey, head, page, one, ceiling, drop, shellfish, clam, oyster, eye, animal legs, eight', '21', '29', 'I was EMPLOYED to give HEAD...when I look back, maybe that was not a wise career move.', 'JH', '1', 'コ', 'かえり.みる', NULL, NULL),
('1166', 'disclose', '啓', '<img src=\"E59593.png\" />', 'disclose, bouncer, door, one, ceiling, flag, taskmaster, mouth', '11', '29', 'Behind closed DOORS, the TASKMASTER tortures to get prisoners to open their MOUTHS and DISCLOSE information.', 'JH', '1', 'ケイ', 'ひら.く、さと.す', NULL, NULL),
('1167', 'show', '示', '<img src=\"E7A4BA.png\" />', 'show, altar, show, two, small', '5', '30', 'A boy made an altar, but he´s afraid to show it to God because he thinks it´s two little.', '5', '3', 'ジ、シ', 'しめ.す', NULL, NULL),
('1168', 'salutation', '礼', '<img src=\"E7A4BC.png\" />', 'salute, salutation, altar, fishhook', '5', '30', 'Indy, my friend, you must be very careful! If you approach the altar and do not give the proper salutation a large fishhook will rip you away.', '3', '3', 'レイ、ライ', '', NULL, NULL),
('1169', 'auspicious', '祥', '<img src=\"E7A5A5.png\" />', 'auspicious, altar, sheep', '10', '30', 'Bringing a sheep to sacrifice on the altar was a sign of an auspicious life. The poor could only afford a pigeon, the more auspicious an expensive sheep for an offering.', 'JH', '1', 'ショウ', 'さいわ.い、きざ.し、よ.い、つまび.らか', NULL, NULL),
('117', 'name', '名', '<img src=\"E5908D.png\" />', 'name, evening, mouth', '6', '7', 'In the evening, when it becomes dark, open your mouth to say your name so that people can recognise you.', '1', '5', 'メイ、ミョウ', 'な、-な', NULL, NULL),
('1170', 'celebrate', '祝', '<img src=\"E7A59D.png\" />', 'celebrate, altar, elder brother, teenager, mouth, human legs', '9', '30', 'It´s a Bar Mitzvah. At the altar, the teenager is singing in his awful, mid-puberty voice. We´ll all celebrate when that part is over!', '4', '2', 'シュク、シュウ', 'いわ.う', NULL, NULL),
('1171', 'blessing', '福', '<img src=\"E7A68F.png\" />', 'blessing, altar, wealth, one, ceiling, mouth, rice field, brains', '13', '30', 'This recalls the selling of indulgences in the history of the Church (As an aside, Protestantism began as a protest of this practice). Basically, one gave wealth to the altar (i.e. priest) and received a blessing. If you prefer a Jewish version, think of the donation (wealth) that is expected when you´re called to the ark (altar in the kanji) to give a blessing over the torah.', '3', '3', 'フク', '', NULL, NULL),
('1172', 'welfare', '祉', '<img src=\"E7A589.png\" />', 'welfare, altar, stop, footprint', '8', '30', 'And in front of every altar, she stopped to pray for the welfare of the others.', 'JH', '1', 'シ', '', NULL, NULL),
('1173', 'company', '社', '<img src=\"E7A4BE.png\" />', 'company, altar, soil, dirt, ground', '7', '30', 'When you enter a Japanese company it´s like you join a cult... your workdesk becomes your altar and you worship the very soil the office is built on.', '2', '4', 'シャ', 'やしろ', NULL, NULL),
('1174', 'inspection', '視', '<img src=\"E8A696.png\" />', 'inspection, altar, see, telescope, eye, human legs', '11', '30', 'The beaurocracy in Japan is such that even altars need to be inspection approved. A little man with glasses comes once a year to give the altar a \"visual once over\" as he calls it (perhaps checking for unauthorised symbology?).', '6', '1', 'シ', 'み.る', NULL, NULL),
('1175', 'Nara', '奈', '<img src=\"E5A588.png\" />', 'nara, large, St. Bernard, altar, show, two, small', '8', '30', 'It´s beautiful place, but the dark side of Nara is that they sacrifice St. Bernards on evil altars every night after the tourists leave!', 'JH', '1', 'ナ、ナイ、ダイ', 'いかん、からなし', NULL, NULL),
('1176', 'military officer', '尉', '<img src=\"E5B089.png\" />', 'military officer, flag, altar, show, two, small, glue', '11', '30', 'Of course it had to be the military officer´s idea to glue a national flag to the altar he´s stationed at.', 'JH', '1', 'イ、ジョウ', '', NULL, NULL),
('1177', 'consolation', '慰', '<img src=\"E685B0.png\" />', 'consolation, military officer, flag, altar, show, two, small, glue, heart', '15', '30', 'A military officer must offer consolation to the hearts of the families of his fallen men.', 'JH', '1', 'イ', 'なぐさ.める、なぐさ.む', NULL, NULL),
('1178', 'goodwill', '款', '<img src=\"E6ACBE.png\" />', 'goodwill, samurai, altar, show, two, small, lack, yawn', '12', '30', 'Samuari, altar, yawn The samurai is on the altar, preaching about goodwill. The audience just yawns however, they want to see the man fight!', 'JH', '1', 'カン', '', NULL, NULL),
('1179', 'prohibition', '禁', '<img src=\"E7A681.png\" />', 'prohibition, grove, tree, wood, altar, show, two, small, tree2, wood2', '13', '30', 'Similar to radical tyro´s story. If you live in Japan, your main exposure to this kanji is probably \"no smoking\" signs. So I imagine the government enacting a prohibition of tobacco, and burning whole groves of tobacco plants on an altar (the altar of public health, or self-righteousness, if you will).', '5', '2', 'キン', '', NULL, NULL),
('118', 'stone', '石', '<img src=\"E79FB3.png\" />', 'stone, cliff, mouth', '5', '7', 'Indiana Jones jumps up and grabs the lip of cliff just in time to evade the huge STONE rolling out of the mouth of the cave!', '1', '3', 'セキ、シャク、コク', 'いし', NULL, NULL),
('1180', 'collar', '襟', '<img src=\"E8A59F.png\" />', 'collar, cloak, prohibition, grove, tree, wood, altar, show, two, small, tree2, wood2', '18', '30', 'A collar is the part of your cloak that, if tightened too tight, will prohibit breathing.', 'JH', '1', 'キン', 'えり', NULL, NULL),
('1181', 'religion', '宗', '<img src=\"E5AE97.png\" />', 'religion, house, altar, show, two, small', '8', '30', 'I never really did figure out what religion my host family was - all I knew was that they kept an altar in their home.', '6', '1', 'シュウ、ソウ', 'むね', NULL, NULL),
('1182', 'adore', '崇', '<img src=\"E5B487.png\" />', 'adore, mountain, religion, house, altar, show, two, small', '11', '30', 'In ancient Greece, it was the religion of the time to adore the gods who live on Mount Olympus.', 'JH', '1', 'スウ', 'あが.める', NULL, NULL),
('1183', 'ritual', '祭', '<img src=\"E7A5AD.png\" />', 'ritual, moon, month, flesh, part of the body, crotch, altar, show, two, small', '11', '30', 'A ritual such as a circumcision: a small piece of flesh from the crotch is left on the altar.', '3', '2', 'サイ', 'まつ.る、まつ.り、まつり', NULL, NULL),
('1184', 'guess', '察', '<img src=\"E5AF9F.png\" />', 'guess, house, ritual, moon, month, flesh, part of the body, crotch, altar, show, two, small', '14', '30', 'I have an informed guess about whose house the dark rituals are performet at.', '4', '3', 'サツ', '', NULL, NULL),
('1185', 'grate', '擦', '<img src=\"E693A6.png\" />', 'grate, finger, fingers, guess, house, ritual, moon, month, flesh, part of the body, crotch, altar, show, two, small', '17', '30', 'If you mis-guess the cheese you´ll grate your fingers on the cheese-grater (happens to me all the time).', 'JH', '1', 'サツ', 'す.る、す.れる、-ず.れ、こす.る、こす.れる', NULL, NULL),
('1186', 'wherefore', '由', '<img src=\"E794B1.png\" />', 'wherefore, sprout, shoot', '5', '30', 'Wherefore art thou, Sprouteo? (Juliet has fallen in love with a brussel sprout) (OR: A brussel sprout has fallen from Juliet´s dinner plate and rolled off).', '3', '3', 'ユ、ユウ、ユイ', 'よし、よ.る', NULL, NULL),
('1187', 'pluck', '抽', '<img src=\"E68ABD.png\" />', 'pluck, finger, fingers, sprout, shoot', '8', '30', '[When I see the word pluck, I think eyebrows, not vegetables. So, to avoid confusing with pick (#733):] Each time this singular, long, wiry black hair starts to sprout out of my chin again, I pluck it with my fingers.', 'JH', '1', 'チュウ', 'ひき-', NULL, NULL),
('1188', 'oil', '油', '<img src=\"E6B2B9.png\" />', 'oil, water, water droplets, water pistol, sprout, shoot', '8', '30', 'The liquid oil that sprouts from an oil field.', '3', '2', 'ユ、ユウ', 'あぶら', NULL, NULL),
('1189', 'sleeve', '袖', '<img src=\"E8A296.png\" />', 'sleeve, cloak, sprout, shoot', '10', '30', 'Imagine some magic cloak, that when worn, has little green sprouts appearing on the sides that grow into sleeves.', 'JH', '', 'シュウ', 'そで', NULL, NULL),
('119', 'resemblance', '肖', '<img src=\"E88296.png\" />', 'resemblance, spark, candle, small, little, moon, month, flesh, part of the body', '7', '7', 'Using DNA matching, a very little bit of flesh can be used to show the resemblence between family members.', 'JH', '1', 'ショウ', 'あやか.る', NULL, NULL),
('1190', 'mid-air', '宙', '<img src=\"E5AE99.png\" />', 'mid-air, house, sprout, shoot', '8', '30', 'Jack´s beanstalk sprouted up, pushed at the roof and lifted the house so that it hangs in mid-air suspended on the SPROUT.', '6', '1', 'チュウ', '', NULL, NULL),
('1191', 'deliver', '届', '<img src=\"E5B18A.png\" />', 'deliver, flag, sprout, shoot', '8', '30', 'In the US, when the mail is delivered, a flag sprouts up on your mailbox. (We don´t have that in Australia.).', '6', '2', 'カイ', 'とど.ける、-とど.け、とど.く', NULL, NULL),
('1192', 'flute', '笛', '<img src=\"E7AC9B.png\" />', 'flute, bamboo, sprout, shoot', '11', '30', 'Flute is made of bamboo sprout.', '3', '1', 'テキ', 'ふえ', NULL, NULL),
('1193', 'axis', '軸', '<img src=\"E8BBB8.png\" />', 'axis, car, sprout, shoot', '12', '30', 'The Germans manufactured so many cars during World War II that it was almost as if they were sprouting from the factories of the Axis.', 'JH', '1', 'ジク', '', NULL, NULL),
('1194', 'armor', '甲', '<img src=\"E794B2.png\" />', 'armour, armor, roots', '5', '30', 'Funny.. this appeared to me as a pictograph of a samurai´s armor. Then I looked up images of the samurai armor and it is not even remotely similar. Then I realised it looks in fact like the belly of the Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles, which I somehow associated with the samurai armor because of the \"turtle samurai\" that appeared earlier. Fits me. The bit that pokes down is to protect the genitals, I guess.', 'JH', '1', 'コウ、カン、カ', 'きのえ', NULL, NULL),
('1195', 'push', '押', '<img src=\"E68ABC.png\" />', 'push, finger, fingers, armour, armor, roots', '8', '30', 'Push the roots down, instead of plucking the seedling.', 'JH', '3', 'オウ', 'お.す、お.し-、お.っ-、お.さえる、おさ.える', NULL, NULL),
('1196', 'headland', '岬', '<img src=\"E5B2AC.png\" />', 'headland, mountain, armour, armor, roots', '8', '30', 'A headland is a mountain that is firmly rooted despite being surrounded on 3 sides by water. (Just like your head is a mountain surrounded by air on 3 sides, a headland!).', 'JH', '1', 'コウ', 'みさき', NULL, NULL),
