('1263', 'department', '科', '<img src=\"E7A791.png\" />', 'department, wheat, cereal, measuring cup, big dipper, The Plough, drop, ten, needle', '9', '31', 'The national DEPARTMENT of WHEATS and MEASURES. Get it? This one was hard until I came up with this.', '2', '3', 'カ', '', NULL, NULL),
('1264', 'map', '図', '<img src=\"E59BB3.png\" />', 'map, pent in, measuring cup, big dipper, The Plough, drop, ten, needle', '7', '31', 'Can´t see direct relation to Big Dipper (#1177) since its writing order is completely different. As raulir noted, it´s written as overlapping at the last stroke of ツ and the first of メ. I take it as a pictograph or treasure map. Two dots represent big trees and the cross (marking the treasure) is placed relative to them.', '2', '4', 'ズ、ト', 'え、はか.る', NULL, NULL),
('1265', 'utilize', '用', '<img src=\"E794A8.png\" />', 'utilize, moon, month, flesh, part of the body, walking stick', '5', '31', 'To tenderize meat in an emergency wilderness situation, just utilize your walking stick!', '2', '4', 'ヨウ', 'もち.いる', NULL, NULL),
('1266', 'comfortable', '庸', '<img src=\"E5BAB8.png\" />', 'commonplace, comfortable, cave, rake, screwdriver, utilise, utilize, moon, month, flesh, part of the body, walking stick', '11', '31', 'To live a comfortable life, single men need only a cave for living, a rake for cleaning and a screwdriver for fixing.', 'JH', '1', 'ヨウ', '', NULL, NULL),
('1267', 'equip', '備', '<img src=\"E58299.png\" />', 'equip, person, flowers, cliff, screwdriver, utilise, utilize, moon, month, flesh, part of the body, walking stick', '12', '31', 'Mr. T wants to climb up and pick the flowers at the top of the cliff. He equips himself with screwdrivers to use as climbing spikes to reach the top of the cliff. Imagine a large AMMO belt full of philips screwdrivers instead of bullets.', '5', '3', 'ビ', 'そな.える、そな.わる、つぶさ.に', NULL, NULL),
('1268', 'once upon a time', '昔', '<img src=\"E69894.png\" />', 'once upon a time, salad, flowers, one, floor, sun, day', '8', '32', 'Once upon a time, the children were forced to eat their salad every day.', '3', '3', 'セキ、シャク', 'むかし', NULL, NULL),
('1269', 'confused', '錯', '<img src=\"E98CAF.png\" />', 'confused, metal, gold, once upon a time, storyteller, salad, sun, day', '16', '32', 'A long time ago, people of the world got confused because there were so many kinds of Metal coins. today we only have the euro.', 'JH', '1', 'サク、シャク', '', NULL, NULL),
('127', 'utensil', '器', '<img src=\"E599A8.png\" />', 'utensil, mouth, large, St. Bernard, mouth4', '15', '7', 'Imagine four hungry mouths all sitting around the table. They are all banging their utensils on the table waiting for a big meal to be placed in the centre.', '4', '1', 'キ', 'うつわ', NULL, NULL),
('1270', 'borrow', '借', '<img src=\"E5809F.png\" />', 'borrow, person, once upon a time, storyteller, salad, sun, day', '10', '32', 'Once upon a time I let Mr T borrow my salad bowl, but he won´t give it back. \"This be mine now, foo!\".', '4', '4', 'シャク', 'か.りる', NULL, NULL),
('1271', 'pity', '惜', '<img src=\"E6839C.png\" />', 'pity, Freud, state of mind, once upon a time, storyteller, salad, sun, day', '11', '32', 'What a pity! My state of mind when i think of the opportunities I missed from once upon a time.', 'JH', '1', 'セキ', 'お.しい、お.しむ', NULL, NULL),
('1272', 'set aside', '措', '<img src=\"E68EAA.png\" />', 'set aside, finger, fingers, once upon a time, storyteller, salad, sun, day', '11', '32', 'Long ago our ancestors set aside the use of fingers and began to use cutlery. (Raichu,11-7-2006) The way I remember it´s 昔 once upon a time (#1184) rather than 旧 olden times (#35) is that they began to use cutlery to eat salad. (I also think about how when you visit the Medieval Times theme park, which is set in Once upon a time, their gimmick is that you eat with your fingers.).', 'JH', '1', 'ソ', 'お.く', NULL, NULL),
('1273', 'scatter', '散', '<img src=\"E695A3.png\" />', 'scatter, salad, moon, month, flesh, part of the body, taskmaster', '12', '32', 'The taskmaster is dissatisfied with the meal she´s served, and scatters the salad & meat across the floor for the servants to clean up.', '4', '3', 'サン', 'ち.る、ち.らす、-ち.らす、ち.らかす、ち.らかる、ばら', NULL, NULL),
('1274', 'twenty', '廿', '<img src=\"E5BBBF.png\" />', 'twenty', '4', '32', 'A generation is 30, one stroke less is twenty.', 'Nam', '', 'ジュウ、ニュウ', 'にじゅう', NULL, NULL),
('1275', 'commoner', '庶', '<img src=\"E5BAB6.png\" />', 'commoner, caverns, cave, twenty, oven-fire, barbecue', '11', '32', 'Commoners have to huddle in caverns around a campfire, while higher class people get heating and central air conditioning in a hotel.', 'JH', '1', 'ショ', '', NULL, NULL),
('1276', 'intercept', '遮', '<img src=\"E981AE.png\" />', 'intercept, commoner, caverns, cave, twenty, oven-fire, barbecue, road', '14', '32', 'The commoners are revolting! We must intercept them on the road before they reach the castle!', 'JH', '1', 'シャ', 'さえぎ.る', NULL, NULL),
('1277', 'seat', '席', '<img src=\"E5B8AD.png\" />', 'seat, caverns, cave, twenty, towel', '10', '32', 'Remember those poor commoners huddled in groups of 20 in a cave? The only thing they had for a seat was some old toweling (while their lords could recline on luxurious couches).', '4', '3', 'セキ', 'むしろ', NULL, NULL),
('1278', 'degrees', '度', '<img src=\"E5BAA6.png\" />', 'degrees, caverns, cave, twenty, crotch', '9', '32', 'The cavern refugees are so poor that they can´t afford thermometers. So, the menfolk expose their crotches inside the cavern, and approximate the temperature in degrees from how shrivelled everything looks downstairs...', '3', '4', 'ド、ト、タク', 'たび、-た.い', NULL, NULL),
('1279', 'transit', '渡', '<img src=\"E6B8A1.png\" />', 'transit, water, water droplets, water pistol, degrees, caverns, cave, twenty, crotch', '12', '32', 'This particular form of transit is a ferry (one of the actual meanings of this character). Naturally it can only cross the water if it´s not frozen, so the temperature must be above 0 degrees.', 'JH', '3', 'ト', 'わた.る、-わた.る、わた.す', NULL, NULL),
('128', 'stinking', '臭', '<img src=\"E887AD.png\" />', 'stinking, nose, drop, eye, large, St. Bernard', '9', '7', 'The ST. BERNARD DOG lifted his large NOSE high in the air to find out where the stinking smell comes from.', 'JH', '1', 'シュウ', 'くさ.い、-くさ.い、にお.う、にお.い', NULL, NULL),
('1280', 'bustle', '奔', '<img src=\"E5A594.png\" />', 'bustle, large, St. Bernard, haystack, ten, needle, needle3, ten3', '8', '32', 'Hustle and bustle = a big St. Bernard dog frisking about in a haystack, knocking it down and spreading the hay about, after the field hands just stacked it up.', 'JH', '1', 'ホン', 'はし.る', NULL, NULL),
('1281', 'erupt', '噴', '<img src=\"E599B4.png\" />', 'erupt, mouth, pitchfork, haystack, ten, needle, shellfish, clam, oyster, eye, animal legs, eight, needle3, ten3', '15', '32', 'History of Pompei: An unexpect eruption and from the mouths of the volcano come lava that threatens the farmers collecting haystacks in the fields and the fisherman catching shells on the coast.', 'JH', '1', 'フン', 'ふ.く', NULL, NULL),
('1282', 'tomb', '墳', '<img src=\"E5A2B3.png\" />', 'tomb, soil, dirt, ground, pitchfork, haystack, ten, needle, shellfish, clam, oyster, eye, animal legs, eight, needle3, ten3', '15', '32', 'After the eruption all is a tomb. The soil has covered the remains of the farmers gathering haystacks and of the fisherman collecting shells.', 'JH', '1', 'フン', '', NULL, NULL),
('1283', 'aroused', '憤', '<img src=\"E686A4.png\" />', 'aroused, Freud, state of mind, pitchfork, haystack, ten, needle, shellfish, clam, oyster, eye, animal legs, eight, needle3, ten3', '15', '32', 'Note: this word in Japanese has the idea of \"indignant\". So aroused here refers to being aroused because of anger over some unjust or wrong act, unfairness etc. It doesn´t seem to carry a meaning associated with arousal in the sense of sex or pleasure. So, my story: think of the angry state of mind aroused at finding all your clams buried under your haystack stolen, gone!', 'JH', '1', 'フン', 'いきどお.る', NULL, NULL),
('1284', 'bake', '焼', '<img src=\"E784BC.png\" />', 'bake, hearth fire, lofty, strawman, wickerman, haystack, ten, needle, one, human legs, needle3, ten3', '12', '32', 'Ah, there´s no better way to bake a pizza than an oven fueled by a burning strawman. And if you listen carefully, there are stifled strawman screams coming from the kitchen. Think of this image: http://users.mtrx.net/funnypics/content/-rdm1-ABCD1234-rdm1-/2005/2005-08-23-0002/Doughboy.jpg.', '4', '2', 'ショウ', 'や.く、や.き、や.き-、-や.き、や.ける', NULL, NULL),
('1285', 'daybreak', '暁', '<img src=\"E69A81.png\" />', 'daybreak, sun, lofty, strawman, wickerman, haystack, ten, needle, one, human legs, needle3, ten3', '12', '32', 'The sun rising beside a straw man in a corn field is a classic cartoon depiction of daybreak.', 'JH', '1', 'ギョウ、キョウ', 'あかつき、さと.る', NULL, NULL),
('1286', 'half', '半', '<img src=\"E58D8A.png\" />', 'half, small, ten, needle', '5', '32', 'Imagine karate chopping the number three in half with a WALKING STICK and pausing the picture just as the first \"board\" breaks.', '2', '5', 'ハン', 'なか.ば', NULL, NULL),
('1287', 'consort', '伴', '<img src=\"E4BCB4.png\" />', 'consort, person, half', '7', '32', 'The person who is your consort is most commonly \"your other half\".', 'JH', '1', 'ハン、バン', 'ともな.う', NULL, NULL),
('1288', 'paddy ridge', '畔', '<img src=\"E79594.png\" />', 'paddy-ridge, rice field, brains, half', '10', '32', 'A PADDY-RIDGE divides the RICE FIELD in HALF.', 'JH', '1', 'ハン', 'あぜ、くろ、ほとり', NULL, NULL),
('1289', 'judgment', '判', '<img src=\"E588A4.png\" />', 'judgement, half, sword, sabre, saber', '7', '32', 'In the bible, King Solomon´s JUDGMENT was admired not by saying to cut the baby in HALF with the SWORD, but that it revealed who the true mother was.', '5', '3', 'ハン、バン', 'わか.る', NULL, NULL),
('129', 'sniff', '嗅', '<img src=\"E59785.png\" />', '', '12', '7', 'Your mouth stinks: you need to sniff your breath.', 'JH', '', 'キュウ', 'か.ぐ', NULL, NULL),
('1290', 'fist', '拳', '<img src=\"E68BB3.png\" />', 'fist, quarter, hand', '10', '32', '1) I hold a roll of quarters in my hand when I make a fist. 2) I hold a quarter in my hand as I prepare to play the Iron Fist Tournament: 鉄拳 （てっけん） at the arcade.', 'JH', '1', 'ケン、ゲン', 'こぶし', NULL, NULL),
('1291', 'ticket', '券', '<img src=\"E588B8.png\" />', 'ticket, quarter, sword, dagger', '8', '32', 'Entering the movie, the dude asks for your ticket, so he can tear it in half. He looks at you funny when you hand him a ticket already torn in half. He quietly tears the stub into quarters after you show him your dagger with a smile.', '5', '2', 'ケン', '', NULL, NULL),
('1292', 'scroll', '巻', '<img src=\"E5B7BB.png\" />', 'scroll, quarter, snake, self', '9', '32', 'At a mysterious bazaar, you happen to come across something interesting: a rolled-up scroll for only 25¢. You buy it up impulsively until you realize that the powerful spell contained within is cursed by a poisonous snake. If you try to cast this spell, the snake will pop out of nowhere and bite you! Hrmph. No wonder it was so cheap...', '6', '2', 'カン、ケン', 'ま.く、まき、ま.き', NULL, NULL),
('1293', 'sphere', '圏', '<img src=\"E59C8F.png\" />', 'sphere, pent in, scroll, quarter, snake, self', '12', '32', 'I assosiate scrolls with spell casting, the efect of this spell is pent in a certain sphere of influence, outside it no damage is done.', 'JH', '1', 'ケン', 'かこ.い', NULL, NULL),
('1294', 'victory', '勝', '<img src=\"E58B9D.png\" />', 'victory, edam, moon, month, flesh, part of the body, quarter, power, muscle, arnold', '12', '32', 'After your VICTORY cut your enemy´s FLESH into QUARTERs to show your POWER.', '3', '3', 'ショウ', 'か.つ、-が.ち、まさ.る、すぐ.れる、かつ', NULL, NULL),
('1295', 'wisteria', '藤', '<img src=\"E897A4.png\" />', 'wisteria, flowers, edam, moon, month, flesh, part of the body, quarter, grains of rice', '18', '32', 'According to legend, the great Ogaki wisteria tree grew and flowered from magical rice grains that were planted under the quarter moon.', 'JH', '1', 'トウ、ドウ', 'ふじ', NULL, NULL),
('1296', 'facsimilie', '謄', '<img src=\"E8AC84.png\" />', 'mimeograph, facsimile, edam, moon, month, flesh, part of the body, quarter, say, words, keitai, mouth', '17', '32', 'Sending a facsimile to the moon can be problematic only a quarter of the words actually get there.', 'JH', '1', 'トウ', '', NULL, NULL),
('1297', 'one-sided', '片', '<img src=\"E78987.png\" />', 'one-sided, waiter with wine on tray', '4', '32', 'Fuaburisu´s pictograph of a man kneeling and presenting the ring to his future wife is a one-sided version of the story. Others say he was giving her the finger.', '6', '2', 'ヘン', 'かた-、かた', NULL, NULL);
