('1327', 'No.', '第', '<img src=\"E7ACAC.png\" />', 'no., bamboo, dollar, bow, stick', '11', '33', 'The No. 1 currency in the world is the dollar. But, the Asian nations are fast catching up and may in reality have already surpassed it. So, let the bamboo represent the No. 2 currencies (the yen, etc.). The reverse order (bamboo on top and the dollar on the bottom) is really a look at the future.', '3', '1', 'ダイ、テイ', '', NULL, NULL),
('1328', 'younger brother', '弟', '<img src=\"E5BC9F.png\" />', 'younger brother, horns, dollar, bow, stick', '7', '33', 'Younger brothers are always more prone to mischief. Mine, you can almost see the little horns on him and the dollar signs on his eyes when he comes up with a money-making scheme.', '2', '4', 'テイ、ダイ、デ', 'おとうと', NULL, NULL),
('1329', 'adroit', '巧', '<img src=\"E5B7A7.png\" />', 'adroit, craft, snare', '5', '33', 'Adroit: dextrous, deft, skillful. Snare is a little generic so I´ll use BEAR TRAP, with huge teeth cartoon style that snares you around the ankle. In the crafting of a bear trap, one must be particularly adroit. Otherwise they will become the victim of their down device.', 'JH', '1', 'コウ', 'たく.み、たく.む、うま.い', NULL, NULL),
('133', 'strange', '奇', '<img src=\"E5A587.png\" />', 'strange, large, St. Bernard, can, mouth, street, nail, spike', '8', '7', 'I find it strange that so many people commit suicide in Tokyo by throwing themselves in front of the train. To me when I look at this kanji, I see a train just about to come out of a tunnel, and above the man waiting for his oppourtunity where he can end it all.', 'JH', '1', 'キ', 'く.しき、あや.しい、くし、めずら.しい', NULL, NULL),
('1330', 'nickname', '号', '<img src=\"E58FB7.png\" />', 'nickname, mouth, snare', '5', '33', 'My nickname is \"No Lips\". Yep, I shouldn´t have put my mouth on that bear trap...', '3', '3', 'ゴウ', 'さけ.ぶ、よびな', NULL, NULL),
('1331', 'decay', '朽', '<img src=\"E69CBD.png\" />', 'decay, tree, wood, snare', '6', '33', 'This snare isn´t terribly effective, because it´s swinging from a decaying tree. Imagine the tree as being so decayed that when an animal gets caught in the snare, its struggles cause the tree to collapse into a putrid mess.', 'JH', '1', 'キュウ', 'く.ちる', NULL, NULL),
('1332', 'boast', '誇', '<img src=\"E8AA87.png\" />', 'boast, say, words, keitai, mouth, Batman, large, St. Bernard, chandelier, one, ceiling, snare', '13', '33', 'The hunter´s boast: I say, it was a \"big one\", but the snare broke and it got away. (credit to many others before).', 'JH', '1', 'コ', 'ほこ.る', NULL, NULL),
('1333', 'chin', '顎', '<img src=\"E9A18E.png\" />', 'chin, mousetrap, mouth, one, ceiling, snare, head, page, one, ceiling, drop, shellfish, clam, oyster, eye, animal legs, eight, mouth2, one2', '18', '33', 'Your chin is the part of your head under your nostrils that forms the double snare that is your jaw.', 'JH', '', 'ガク', 'あご、あぎと', NULL, NULL),
