('159', 'lake', '湖', '<img src=\"E6B996.png\" />', 'lake, water, water droplets, water pistol, uncivilized, zombie, old, tombstone, gravestone, church, ten, needle, mouth, moon, month, flesh, part of the body', '12', '8', 'This is my favorite story. Simply associate the sad moment of an OLD person, standing near the WATER of the lake and looking at the MOON reflected in the lake. The created primitives themselves are put so beautifully, that you will not forget this kanji.', '3', '2', 'コ', 'みずうみ', NULL, NULL),
('1590', 'mochi', '餅', '<img src=\"E9A485.png\" />', 'mochi, eat, food, umbrella, good, halo, drop, silver, puzzle, horns, two hands', '14', '38', 'Call your friend and he answers the phone \"Mochi, mochi!\" whatever he is eating sure is making it hard to understand. I will puzzle over the content of our conversation for some time to come.', 'JH', '', 'ヘイ、ヒョウ', 'もち、もちい', NULL, NULL),
('1591', 'foster', '養', '<img src=\"E9A48A.png\" />', 'foster, sheep, eat, food, umbrella, good, halo, drop, silver', '15', '38', 'A sheep became the foster parent for a wolf pup, feeding it with milk. This story cannot end well...', '4', '1', 'ヨウ、リョウ', 'やしな.う', NULL, NULL),
('1592', 'sated', '飽', '<img src=\"E9A3BD.png\" />', 'sated, eat, food, umbrella, good, halo, drop, silver, wrap, bound up, snake, self', '13', '38', 'My gluttony was only sated after I ate the hamburger AND the wrapper!', 'JH', '1', 'ホウ', 'あ.きる、あ.かす、あ.く', NULL, NULL),
('1593', 'previously', '既', '<img src=\"E697A2.png\" />', 'previously, silver, waitress', '10', '38', 'Distinguish from formerly (#501). Think of previously as \"the previous customer\" in a restaurant. At a cheap sleazy diner, the waitress gives you unwashed silverware that was previously used by the previous customer. Yuck.', 'JH', '1', 'キ', 'すで.に', NULL, NULL),
('1594', 'outline', '概', '<img src=\"E6A682.png\" />', 'outline, roots, tree, wood, silver, waitress, previously', '14', '38', 'The police tried to draw a chalk outline around the dead waitress, but it was kinda tough with all the tree roots underneath her.', 'JH', '1', 'ガイ', 'おうむ.ね', NULL, NULL),
('1595', 'rue', '慨', '<img src=\"E685A8.png\" />', 'rue, regret, resentment, Freud, state of mind, silver, waitress, previously', '13', '38', 'If you don´t leave some silver as a tip, you will rue the day you earned the resentment of your waitress.', 'JH', '1', 'ガイ', '', NULL, NULL),
('1596', 'even', '平', '<img src=\"E5B9B3.png\" />', 'even, water-lily, lily pad', '5', '39', 'There´s an even covering of water lilies on the pond at 金閣寺（きんかくじ） the Golden Pavilion in Kyoto.', '3', '3', 'ヘイ、ビョウ、ヒョウ', 'たい.ら、-だいら、ひら、ひら-', NULL, NULL),
('1597', 'call', '呼', '<img src=\"E591BC.png\" />', 'call, mouth, even, water-lily, lily pad, question mark', '8', '39', '\'Budd\' - \'weis\' - \'er\' call the frogs mouths from the liliy pads, working to get you hooked on beer.', '6', '3', 'コ', 'よ.ぶ', NULL, NULL),
('1598', 'two-mat area', '坪', '<img src=\"E59DAA.png\" />', 'two-mat area, soil, dirt, ground, even, water-lily, lily pad', '8', '39', 'A two-mat area is just about as much ground as you will need for a lily pond.', 'JH', '1', 'ヘイ', 'つぼ', NULL, NULL),
('1599', 'evaluate', '評', '<img src=\"E8A995.png\" />', 'evaluate, say, words, keitai, mouth, even, water-lily, lily pad', '12', '39', 'Good evaluation should always be words of even fairness.', '5', '1', 'ヒョウ', '', NULL, NULL),
('16', 'old', '古', '<img src=\"E58FA4.png\" />', 'old, tombstone, gravestone, church, ten, needle, mouth', '5', '2', 'Tombstone and cross on an old man´s grave.', '2', '4', 'コ', 'ふる.い、ふる-、-ふる.す', NULL, NULL),
('160', 'fathom', '測', '<img src=\"E6B8AC.png\" />', 'fathom, water, water droplets, water pistol, rule, shellfish, clam, oyster, eye, animal legs, eight, sword, sabre, saber', '12', '8', 'A fathom is the unit you use when making rules about water´s depth.', '5', '2', 'ソク', 'はか.る', NULL, NULL),
('1600', 'reap', '刈', '<img src=\"E58888.png\" />', 'reap, sheaf, sword, sabre, saber', '4', '39', 'A SABRE is used to cut the stalks of plants being REAPED at harvest. They are then combined into a SHEAF.', 'JH', '1', 'ガイ、カイ', 'か.る', NULL, NULL),
('1601', 'moment', '刹', '<img src=\"E588B9.png\" />', 'moment, sheaf, tree, wood, sword, sabre, saber', '8', '39', 'The kendo artist takes a brief moment to practice his skills: he throws sheafs over the tree and tries to cut them with his saber when they come down again.', 'JH', '', 'セチ、セツ、サツ', '', NULL, NULL),
('1602', 'hope', '希', '<img src=\"E5B88C.png\" />', 'hope, sheaf, linen, by one’s side, towel', '7', '39', 'I hope this works, you say as you stuff a sheaf of stalks under your blanket but above your linens. Your real hope is that your parents don´t find out that you left the house.', '4', '2', 'キ、ケ', 'まれ', NULL, NULL),
('1603', 'villain', '凶', '<img src=\"E587B6.png\" />', 'villain, sheaf, shovel', '4', '39', 'Here the villain digs a hole with a shovel and covers it with a sheaf, hoping someone will fall in.', 'JH', '1', 'キョウ', '', NULL, NULL),
('1604', 'bosom', '胸', '<img src=\"E883B8.png\" />', 'bosom, moon, month, flesh, part of the body, bound up, villain, sheaf, shovel', '10', '39', 'Just think of the heroine\'s bosom in a movie. The villain ties up the heroine (to the traintracks or the conveyor belt etc) but her bosom is the body part that is always left sticking out.', '6', '2', 'キョウ', 'むね、むな-', NULL, NULL),
('1605', 'detach', '離', '<img src=\"E99BA2.png\" />', 'detach, sheik, top hat, villain, sheaf, shovel, belt, elbow, turkey', '18', '39', 'I´ve finally met my arch-rival, the evilest of all villains. Finally, I´m about to fight him. But what´s this? He´s suspiciously quiet. I move to attack him, and his right arm falls off at the elbow. Strange. I walk up to him and detach his left arm. Very strange. I undo his belt, and take off his top hat... BLAST! It was just a decoy turkey!', 'JH', '1', 'リ', 'はな.れる、はな.す', NULL, NULL),
('1606', 'crystal', '璃', '<img src=\"E79283.png\" />', 'crystal, king, jewel, ball, sheik, top hat, villain, sheaf, shovel, belt, elbow', '14', '39', 'Michael Jackson is the king of pop, wearing his crystal rhinestone glove (see detach (#1492).', 'JH', '1', 'リ', '', NULL, NULL),
('1607', 'kill', '殺', '<img src=\"E6AEBA.png\" />', 'kill, sheaf, tree, wood, cruise missile, missile, wind, crotch', '10', '39', 'X marks the spot on the tree where the missile hit. No doubt, it was meant to kill us.', '4', '3', 'サツ、サイ、セツ', 'ころ.す、-ごろ.し、そ.ぐ', NULL, NULL),
('1608', 'bracing', '爽', '<img src=\"E788BD.png\" />', 'bracing, large, St. Bernard, sheaf, sheaf4', '11', '39', 'The St Bernard is bracing itself for an operation requiring four stitches.', 'JH', '1', 'ソウ', 'あき.らか、さわ.やか、たがう', NULL, NULL),
('1609', 'genuine', '純', '<img src=\"E7B494.png\" />', 'genuine, thread, spiderman, earthworm, drop, shovel, fishhook', '10', '39', 'For remembering the primitive earthworm: Drops of rain were falling so I took my shovel to dig up some earthworms to put them on my fishook..... My story: To have a genuine fishing line you don\'t just pick up a stick but you also attach some thread onto it and at the end an earthworm must be hung.', '6', '2', 'ジュン', '', NULL, NULL),
('161', 'soil', '土', '<img src=\"E59C9F.png\" />', 'soil, dirt, ground', '3', '8', 'Remembering soil is easy. If soil is soft, you can take a walking stick and plunge it two* feet into the ground.', '1', '5', 'ド、ト', 'つち', NULL, NULL),
('1610', 'immediate', '頓', '<img src=\"E9A093.png\" />', 'immediate, earthworm, drop, shovel, fishhook, head, page, one, ceiling, drop, shellfish, clam, oyster, eye, animal legs, eight', '13', '39', 'Ever chopped the head off an earthworm? Notice how it will grow back immediately! Beware the killer earthworms...', 'JH', '', 'トン、トツ', 'にわか.に、とん.と、つまず.く、とみ.に、ぬかずく', NULL, NULL),
('1611', 'dull', '鈍', '<img src=\"E9888D.png\" />', 'dull, metal, gold, earthworm, drop, shovel, fishhook', '12', '39', 'The metal hook is too dull to even pierce an earthworm....', 'JH', '2', 'ドン', 'にぶ.い、にぶ.る、にぶ-、なま.る、なまく.ら', NULL, NULL),
('1612', 'spicy', '辛', '<img src=\"E8BE9B.png\" />', 'spicy, stand up, vase, ten, needle', '7', '39', 'Eating spicy food makes you stand up ten times faster than usual, ´cause you just need to get something to drink!', 'JH', '2', 'シン', 'から.い、つら.い、-づら.い、かのと', NULL, NULL),
('1613', 'resign', '辞', '<img src=\"E8BE9E.png\" />', 'resign, tongue, thousand, mouth, spicy, stand up, vase, ten, needle', '13', '39', 'This guy´s job is tasting the spicy curry at the local Indian Food Factory. He has to resign from his job before his tongue is rendered completely useless after all the spicy food that he has to try all day long...', '4', '3', 'ジ', 'や.める、いな.む', NULL, NULL),
('1614', 'catalpa', '梓', '<img src=\"E6A293.png\" />', 'catalpa, tree, wood, spicy, stand up, vase, ten, needle', '11', '39', 'The CATALPA is the tree that bears the SPICY Indian bean (NOTE - The Catalpa is also known as the \"Indian Bean\" due to the bean pods that grow from it).', 'Nam', '1', 'シ', 'あずさ', NULL, NULL),
('1615', 'superintend', '宰', '<img src=\"E5AEB0.png\" />', 'superintend, house, spicy, stand up, vase, ten, needle', '10', '39', 'The superintendent of a Japanese school district needs a spicy relationship at home after watching girls in miniskirts all day.', 'JH', '1', 'サイ', '', NULL, NULL),
('1616', 'wall', '壁', '<img src=\"E5A381.png\" />', 'wall, ketchup, flag, mouth, spicy, stand up, vase, ten, needle, soil, dirt, ground', '16', '39', 'Did anyone else used to put ketchup packets on the ground and jump on them so they spattered on the wall?', 'JH', '1', 'ヘキ', 'かべ', NULL, NULL),
('1617', 'holed gem', '璧', '<img src=\"E792A7.png\" />', '', '18', '39', 'Even more valuable and perfect (完璧) than a holed gem is a delicious meatball (ball = たま = 玉) with ketchup. Yum!', 'JH', '', 'ヘキ', 'たま', NULL, NULL),
('1618', 'evade', '避', '<img src=\"E981BF.png\" />', 'evade, ketchup, flag, mouth, spicy, stand up, vase, ten, needle, road', '16', '39', 'You can try and evade them, but they´ll ketchup with you on the road... Sorry, couldn´t resist it.', 'JH', '1', 'ヒ', 'さ.ける、よ.ける', NULL, NULL),
('1619', 'new', '新', '<img src=\"E696B0.png\" />', 'new, red pepper, stand up, vase, tree, wood, axe', '13', '39', 'Don\'t confuse left primitive with catalpa (#1498). Every time the farmer cuts down the peppers from the red pepper plant, he has to use a brand new axe. This is because the spicy peppers cause the metal to erode very quickly, thereby rendering the axe completely useless.', '2', '4', 'シン', 'あたら.しい、あら.た、あら-、にい-', NULL, NULL),
('162', 'spit', '吐', '<img src=\"E59090.png\" />', 'spit, mouth, soil, dirt, ground', '6', '8', 'The only things that come out of my MOUTH and onto the GROUND are spit and vomit. Everything else (words, song) floats on the air.', 'JH', '1', 'ト', 'は.く、つ.く', NULL, NULL),
('1620', 'firewood', '薪', '<img src=\"E896AA.png\" />', 'fuel, firewood, flowers, new, red pepper, stand up, vase, tree, wood, axe', '16', '39', 'New flowers grow in areas of forests which have been chopped down for firewood.', 'JH', '1', 'シン', 'たきぎ、まき', NULL, NULL),
('1621', 'parent', '親', '<img src=\"E8A6AA.png\" />', 'parent, red pepper, stand up, vase, tree, wood, see, telescope, eye, human legs', '16', '39', 'A wise parent lets their kids learn. A kid wants to try to eat the red pepper plant, the wise parent says \"Try it and see for yourself\".', '2', '4', 'シン', 'おや、おや-、した.しい、した.しむ', NULL, NULL),
('1622', 'happiness', '幸', '<img src=\"E5B9B8.png\" />', 'happiness, ten, needle, stand up, vase, ten, needle, ten2, needle2', '8', '39', 'Happiness adds a bit (or ten) of spice to your life.', '3', '3', 'コウ', 'さいわ.い、さち、しあわ.せ', NULL, NULL),
('1623', 'tenacious', '執', '<img src=\"E59FB7.png\" />', 'tenacious, happiness, ten, needle, stand up, vase, fat man, musashimaru, nine, baseball, drop, ten2, needle2', '11', '39', 'Tenacious-D is happy band led by a fat man. (It´s Tenacious-D time, ya muthafucka´, gwaoh!).', 'JH', '1', 'シツ、シュウ', 'と.る', NULL, NULL),
('1624', 'clasp', '摯', '<img src=\"E691AF.png\" />', '', '15', '39', 'When you clasp something you tenaciously 執 hold on to it with your hand 手, te. 真摯、しんし, sincerity, earnestness.', 'JH', '', 'シ', 'いた.る', NULL, NULL),
('1625', 'report', '報', '<img src=\"E5A0B1.png\" />', 'report, happiness, ten, needle, stand up, vase, underpants, stamp, crotch, ten2, needle2', '12', '39', 'Recall the fashion model wearing just a stamp over his crotch (clothing (#1399)). When he got happy, of course, it ended up in the news report.', '5', '3', 'ホウ', 'むく.いる', NULL, NULL),
('1626', 'shout', '叫', '<img src=\"E58FAB.png\" />', 'shout, mouth, cornucopia', '6', '39', 'There was a man in a village who had a special gift : whenever he shouted and screamed, his mouth became a cornucopia, overflowing with fruits and food of all sorts. Many of the locals thought he was a cruel man, always screaming at his wife, until they realised he was in fact very kind, and his gift brought prosperity to his family.', 'JH', '2', 'キョウ', 'さけ.ぶ', NULL, NULL),
('1627', 'twist', '糾', '<img src=\"E7B3BE.png\" />', 'twist, thread, spiderman, cornucopia', '9', '39', 'A cornucopia is a twisted goat\'s horn decorated with coloured threads.', 'JH', '1', 'キュウ', 'ただ.す', NULL, NULL),
('1628', 'income', '収', '<img src=\"E58F8E.png\" />', 'income, cornucopia, crotch', '4', '39', 'Prostitutes can make a veritable cornucopia of income by using their crotches -- they put the \"come\" in \"income.\" (A bit lewd perhaps, but effective in keeping this character distinct from similar keywords like profit (#906) or earnings (#893)).', '6', '3', 'シュウ', 'おさ.める、おさ.まる', NULL, NULL),
('1629', 'lowly', '卑', '<img src=\"E58D91.png\" />', 'lowly, Wayne Slob, drop, rice field, brains, cornucopia, ten, needle', '9', '39', 'Lowly people only have a drop of brains and use nothing but 4-letter words.', 'JH', '1', 'ヒ', 'いや.しい、いや.しむ、いや.しめる', NULL, NULL),
('163', 'pressure', '圧', '<img src=\"E59CA7.png\" />', 'pressure, cliff, soil, dirt, ground', '5', '8', 'The GROUND at the base of a CLIFF must suffer from enormous pressure.', '5', '2', 'アツ、エン、オウ', 'お.す、へ.す、おさ.える、お.さえる', NULL, NULL),
('1630', 'tombstone', '碑', '<img src=\"E7A291.png\" />', 'tombstone, stone, rock, lowly, Wayne Slob, drop, rice field, brains, cornucopia, ten, needle', '14', '39', 'There is a grave of a lowly man with a tombstone made of a simple, small stone. If you bow really low you can read the very small inscription engraved on the stone, it says - “Now that you bowed so low to read this, you are as lowly as I once was”.', 'JH', '1', 'ヒ', 'いしぶみ', NULL, NULL),
('1631', 'land', '陸', '<img src=\"E999B8.png\" />', 'land, pinnacle, parthenon, acropolis, mini-tractor, rice seedlings, soil, dirt, ground, human legs, soil2, dirt2, ground2', '11', '39', 'My rice-seedlings have become sentient and will go on a mission. I can only apologise for the next 6 frames. In the distance, there is a pinnacle, which the newly-awakened rice-seedlings who are still stuck in the ground can see. Could it be the Promised Land?', '4', '2', 'リク、ロク', 'おか', NULL, NULL),
('1632', 'intimate', '睦', '<img src=\"E79DA6.png\" />', 'intimate, eye, mini-tractor, rice seedlings, soil, dirt, ground, human legs, soil2, dirt2, ground2', '13', '39', 'The farmer was never very intimate with his wife. He always kept his eye on his precious rice seedlings in the soil.', 'JH', '1', 'ボク、モク', 'むつ.まじい、むつ.む、むつ.ぶ', NULL, NULL),
('1633', 'forces', '勢', '<img src=\"E58BA2.png\" />', 'forces, mini-tractor, rice seedlings, soil, dirt, ground, human legs, fat man, musashimaru, round, nine, baseball, drop, power, muscle, arnold, soil2, dirt2, ground2', '13', '39', 'What power makes rice seedlings in the ground grow into well rounded plants? The forces of nature.', '5', '2', 'セイ、ゼイ', 'いきお.い、はずみ', NULL, NULL),
('1634', 'heat', '熱', '<img src=\"E786B1.png\" />', 'heat, mini-tractor, rice seedlings, soil, dirt, ground, human legs, fat man, musashimaru, round, nine, baseball, drop, oven-fire, barbecue, soil2, dirt2, ground2', '15', '39', 'Heat up those RICE SEEDLINGS you pulled from the SOIL in a ROUND pan over a low FLAME. (Note: the hot pan image helps reinforce the idea that this kanji for \"atsui\" refers to something hot to the touch, as opposed to hot weather).', '4', '3', 'ネツ', 'あつ.い', NULL, NULL),
('1635', 'diamond', '菱', '<img src=\"E88FB1.png\" />', 'diamond, flowers, Mao, soil, dirt, ground, human legs, walking legs', '11', '39', 'Some girls want diamonds, but others will be satisfied with just flowers. However if you think you can win her over with rice seedlings, expect her to get up on her walking legs and walk on out!', 'Nam', '', 'リョウ', 'ひし', NULL, NULL),
('1636', 'mausoleum', '陵', '<img src=\"E999B5.png\" />', 'mausoleum, pinnacle, parthenon, acropolis, Mao, soil, dirt, ground, human legs, walking legs', '11', '39', 'Ancient Japanese built a mausoleum for the \"unknown rice farmer\". It\'s on the pinnacle of Mt. Fuji, and it has a statue of a guy with huge walking legs planting rice seedlings as he goes.', 'JH', '1', 'リョウ', 'みささぎ', NULL, NULL),
('1637', 'sign of the hog', '亥', '<img src=\"E4BAA5.png\" />', 'sign of the hog, acorn, top hat', '6', '39', 'A greedy hog in a top hat who has eaten all of the acorns. He even elbows people out of the way to get them.', 'Nam', '1', 'ガイ、カイ', 'い', NULL, NULL),
('1638', 'nucleus', '核', '<img src=\"E6A0B8.png\" />', 'nucleus, tree, wood, sign of the hog, acorn, top hat', '10', '39', 'In the nucleus of the acorn, all the DNA is stored -- the building blocks for a new tree.', 'JH', '1', 'カク', '', NULL, NULL),
