('1702', 'sigh', '嘆', '<img src=\"E59886.png\" />', 'sigh, mouth, scarecrow, flowers, mouth, husband', '13', '40', 'A sigh escapes the mouth of the scarecrow, who laments: \"...if I only had a brain, I could learn kanji\".', 'JH', '1', 'タン', 'なげ.く、なげ.かわしい', NULL, NULL),
('1703', 'difficult', '難', '<img src=\"E99BA3.png\" />', 'difficult, scarecrow, flowers, mouth, husband, turkey', '18', '40', 'Learning Kanji is difficult for Turkeys.', '6', '3', 'ナン', 'かた.い、-がた.い、むずか.しい、むづか.しい、むつか.しい、-にく.い', NULL, NULL),
('1704', 'splendor', '華', '<img src=\"E88FAF.png\" />', 'splendor, flowers, silage, ten, needle', '10', '40', 'The Queen of England taking a walk round a village: ´Excuse me, I couldn´t help noticing the splendour of the flowers in your garden. Simply splendid. Ten out of ten.´ The villager gruffly replies: ´No it ´aint. It´s all muck. An´ I´m gonna cut it all down and sell it to the farmer for silage.´.', 'JH', '1', 'カ、ケ', 'はな', NULL, NULL),
('1705', 'droop', '垂', '<img src=\"E59E82.png\" />', 'droop, drop, silage, walking cane, stick, one, floor', '8', '40', 'The thousand head of cattle let their heads droop as they devour the silage (animal fodder) that is lying on the floor around them.', '6', '1', 'スイ', 'た.れる、た.らす、た.れ、-た.れ、なんなんと.す', NULL, NULL),
('1706', 'saliva', '唾', '<img src=\"E594BE.png\" />', 'saliva, mouth, droop, drop, silage, one, floor', '11', '40', 'When some people are sleeping, their mouths droop open, and saliva drips out.', 'JH', '', 'ダ、タ', 'つば、つばき', NULL, NULL),
('1707', 'drowsy', '睡', '<img src=\"E79DA1.png\" />', 'drowsy, eye, droop, drop, silage, walking cane, stick, one, floor', '13', '40', 'Our eyes droop when we are drowsy.', 'JH', '1', 'スイ', '', NULL, NULL),
('1708', 'spindle', '錘', '<img src=\"E98C98.png\" />', 'spindle, metal, gold, droop, drop, silage, walking cane, stick, one, floor', '16', '40', 'Wasn´t it a cursed spindle that Sleeping Beauty pricked her finger on? Therefore the spindle was the metal that caused her to droop and eventually sleep for 100 years.', 'Nam', '1', 'スイ', 'つむ、おもり', NULL, NULL),
('1709', 'ride', '乗', '<img src=\"E4B997.png\" />', 'ride, wheat, cereal, silage', '9', '40', 'It´s a hay ride! You sit on piles of silage and everyone likes to imitate old-time farmers with a piece of wheat sticking out of their mouths.', '3', '3', 'ジョウ、ショウ', 'の.る、-の.り、の.せる', NULL, NULL),
('171', 'time', '時', '<img src=\"E69982.png\" />', 'time, sun, day, Buddhist temple, soil, dirt, ground, glue', '10', '8', 'When the SUN starts to shine on the TEMPLE, it´s time to get up.', '2', '5', 'ジ', 'とき、-どき', NULL, NULL),
('1710', 'surplus', '剰', '<img src=\"E589B0.png\" />', 'surplus, ride, wheat, cereal, silage, sword, sabre, saber', '11', '40', 'If you go for a ride and find a saber beside you, perhaps you got into an Army surplus jeep.', 'JH', '1', 'ジョウ', 'あまつさえ、あま.り、あま.る', NULL, NULL),
('1711', 'now', '今', '<img src=\"E4BB8A.png\" />', 'now, meeting, umbrella, one, 7', '4', '41', 'My MEETING is at 7- but that´s NOW!', '2', '5', 'コン、キン', 'いま', NULL, NULL),
('1712', 'include', '含', '<img src=\"E590AB.png\" />', 'include, now, clock, mouth', '7', '41', 'This clock includes a mouth that will tell you what the time is now. Hearing impaired people have this kind of watches... now imagine them as a big mouth under the clock.', 'JH', '2', 'ガン', 'ふく.む、ふく.める', NULL, NULL),
('1713', 'covet', '貪', '<img src=\"E8B2AA.png\" />', '', '11', '41', 'Whatever you covet at the moment (now), can be bought with money. Well, _almost_ anything....', 'JH', '', 'タン、 トン', 'むさぼ.る', NULL, NULL),
('1714', 'versify', '吟', '<img src=\"E5909F.png\" />', 'versify, mouth, now, clock', '7', '41', 'Versify this kanji as follows: Hickery dickery dock, the mouth ran by the clock.', 'JH', '1', 'ギン', '', NULL, NULL),
('1715', 'wish', '念', '<img src=\"E5BFB5.png\" />', 'wish, now, clock, heart', '8', '41', 'Someone wishing from the bottom of their heart that the clock would stop. A mid-life crisis perhaps.', '4', '3', 'ネン', '', NULL, NULL),
('1716', 'wrench', '捻', '<img src=\"E68DBB.png\" />', 'wrenching, finger, fingers, wish, wishbone, now, clock, heart', '11', '41', 'Ever try WRENCHING a bolt with just your FINGERS? Trust me, you´ll WISH you had a wrench for WRENCHING to save your FINGERS.', 'JH', '', 'ネン、ジョウ', 'ね.じる、ねじ.る、ひね.くる、ひね.る', NULL, NULL),
('1717', 'harp', '琴', '<img src=\"E790B4.png\" />', 'harp, king, jewel, ball, now, clock, king2, jewel2, ball2', '12', '41', 'Two kings were fighting over a beautiful koto (harp). So they had a clock built into it that would measure how long each one played it. That way they could be sure none played it more than othe other.', 'JH', '1', 'キン', 'こと', NULL, NULL),
('1718', 'shade', '陰', '<img src=\"E999B0.png\" />', 'shade, pinnacle, parthenon, acropolis, now, clock, rising cloud, two, elbow, wall', '11', '41', 'There are three types of shade: 1. natural (a high pinnacle), 2. man-made buildings (a clock tower), 3. meteorological (a cloud).', 'JH', '1', 'イン', 'かげ、かげ.る', NULL, NULL),
('1719', 'beforehand', '予', '<img src=\"E4BA88.png\" />', 'beforehand, halberd with stroke missing', '4', '41', 'Beforehand, this was a halberd but I cut it short so it could be for hand to hand combat.', '3', '3', 'ヨ、シャ', 'あらかじ.め', NULL, NULL),
('172', 'level', '均', '<img src=\"E59D87.png\" />', 'level, soil, dirt, ground, ladle, drop, drop2', '7', '8', 'Soil is scooped up into a ladel. The extra drop is brushed off to make it level.', '5', '2', 'キン', 'なら.す', NULL, NULL),
('1720', 'preface', '序', '<img src=\"E5BA8F.png\" />', 'preface, cave, beforehand', '7', '41', 'The preface to all human history was written beforehand in caves.', '5', '1', 'ジョ', 'つい.で、ついで', NULL, NULL),
('1721', 'deposit', '預', '<img src=\"E9A090.png\" />', 'deposit, beforehand, head, page, one, ceiling, drop, shellfish, clam, oyster, eye, animal legs, eight', '13', '41', 'Depositing money into your savings account is something you do beforehand if you use your head. If you´re in Japan your passbook says 預金機（よきんき）when you make a deposit.', '5', '2', 'ヨ', 'あず.ける、あず.かる', NULL, NULL),
('1722', 'plains', '野', '<img src=\"E9878E.png\" />', 'plains, computer, beforehand', '11', '41', 'These days we all work in front of computers. Beforehand we all worked out in the fields, in the plains.', '2', '4', 'ヤ、ショ', 'の、の-', NULL, NULL),
('1723', 'concurrently', '兼', '<img src=\"E585BC.png\" />', 'concurrently, animal horns, rake, stick, stick2', '10', '41', 'Our ninja hero, disguised as a gardener with a rake, is suddenly attacked from both left and right concurrently by bulls with animal horns. Our hero lets out a blood-curdling scream and tears his rake handle vertically in half, so he now has two wooden staffs (split rake handle) to fight with. He grips each staff (left side and right side) and rams it into the horns of the charging bulls. The force of each charging bull causes the tips of each staff to split again (split bottom of each rake handle).', 'JH', '1', 'ケン', 'か.ねる、-か.ねる', NULL, NULL),
('1724', 'dislike', '嫌', '<img src=\"E5AB8C.png\" />', 'dislike, woman, concurrently, animal horns, rake', '13', '41', 'Naturally, if you´re dating more than one woman concurrently, they will certainly dislike each other!', 'JH', '1', 'ケン、ゲン', 'きら.う、きら.い、いや', NULL, NULL),
('1725', 'sickle', '鎌', '<img src=\"E98E8C.png\" />', 'sickle, metal, gold, concurrently, animal horns, rake', '18', '41', 'This is a special sickle with metal blades on both sides. It can cut many things concurrently!', 'JH', '1', 'レン、ケン', 'かま', NULL, NULL),
('1726', 'self-effacing', '謙', '<img src=\"E8AC99.png\" />', 'self-effacing, say, words, keitai, mouth, concurrently, animal horns, rake', '17', '41', 'When you are self-effacing you use words to concurrently bring yourself down and make yourself look better.', 'JH', '1', 'ケン', '', NULL, NULL),
('1727', 'bargain', '廉', '<img src=\"E5BB89.png\" />', 'bargain, cave, concurrently, animal horns, rake', '13', '41', 'Stores don´t want you to know it, but if you find the secret cave, they run bargains there concurrently to their regular prices. (Image: pulling a certain level in a store to find the \"bargain cave).', 'JH', '1', 'レン', '', NULL, NULL),
('1728', 'west', '西', '<img src=\"E8A5BF.png\" />', 'west, one, four', '6', '41', 'The old west represented by a completely empty whiskey bottle (compare sign of the bird (#1427) whiskey bottle about one third full).', '2', '5', 'セイ、サイ、ス', 'にし', NULL, NULL),
('1729', 'value', '価', '<img src=\"E4BEA1.png\" />', 'value, person, old west', '8', '41', 'In the West, people have no value. Only money is important.', '5', '1', 'カ、ケ', 'あたい', NULL, NULL),
('173', 'fire', '火', '<img src=\"E781AB.png\" />', 'fire', '4', '8', 'For some reason, this kanji reminds me of a person running, her arms (the two drops) raised up, because she caught on fire!', '1', '5', 'カ', 'ひ、-び、ほ-', NULL, NULL),
('1730', 'need', '要', '<img src=\"E8A681.png\" />', 'need, old west, woman', '9', '41', '(ヨウ) When Clint needs a woman, he likes to be on top.', '4', '3', 'ヨウ', 'い.る', NULL, NULL),
('1731', 'loins', '腰', '<img src=\"E885B0.png\" />', 'loins, moon, month, flesh, part of the body, need, old west, woman', '13', '41', 'If you want to get closer to the actual meaning, then I think that 腰(こし) is more like the hips or the small of the back. After being sat down in the office too long, people often say 腰がいたい！It´s the part of the body that needs massaging.', 'JH', '2', 'ヨウ', 'こし', NULL, NULL),
('1732', 'ballot', '票', '<img src=\"E7A5A8.png\" />', 'ballot, old west, altar, show, two, small', '11', '41', 'In the Old West there were no ballot boxes. Afraid of fraud and fighting among the gunslingers, the ballots were posted into a slot in the top of the local church altar instead. They may have been rough, but the cowboys wouldn´t fight in the church.', '4', '1', 'ヒョウ', '', NULL, NULL),
('1733', 'drift', '漂', '<img src=\"E6BC82.png\" />', 'drift, water, water droplets, water pistol, ballot, old west, altar, show, two, small', '14', '41', 'In Florida, Bush through Kerry´s ballots into the water, watching them drift away and setting the whole country adrift.', 'JH', '1', 'ヒョウ', 'ただよ.う', NULL, NULL),
('1734', 'signpost', '標', '<img src=\"E6A899.png\" />', 'signpost, tree, wood, ballot, old west, altar, show, two, small', '15', '41', 'Trees were frequenly used as signposts in those days, indicating where one had to go to cast their ballots.', '4', '1', 'ヒョウ', 'しるべ、しるし', NULL, NULL),
('1735', 'chestnut', '栗', '<img src=\"E6A097.png\" />', 'chestnut, old west, tree, wood', '10', '41', 'Chestnut tree, west nut tree.', 'Nam', '1', 'リツ、リ', 'くり、おののく', NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `kanjis` (`ID_Kanji`, `K_Keyword`, `K_Kanji`, `K_StrokeDiagram`, `K_Constituent`, `K_StrokeCount`, `K_LessonNo`, `K_Story`, `K_JouYou`, `K_JLPT`, `K_OnYomi`, `K_KunYomi`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
('1736', 'shudder', '慄', '<img src=\"E68584.png\" />', '', '13', '41', 'Shudder. If chestnut trees were sentient, shudder would be their state of mind as the tree shaker approaches. Note: Tree shakers are used commercially to harvest nuts and cider apples. A tree shaker makes a tree shudder causing all the ripe chestnuts to fall.', 'JH', '', 'リツ', 'おそ.れる、 おのの.く、 ふる.える', NULL, NULL),
('1737', 'transition', '遷', '<img src=\"E981B7.png\" />', 'transition, old west, large, St. Bernard, snake, self, road', '15', '41', 'Since the days of the Old West, traveling has transitioned from trying not to step on big snakes to driving on big roads.', 'JH', '1', 'セン', 'うつ.る、うつ.す、みやこがえ', NULL, NULL),
('1738', 'capsize', '覆', '<img src=\"E8A686.png\" />', 'capsize, old west, restore, Nelson, column, going, line, fold back, double back, reclining, lying down, sun, day, walking legs', '18', '41', 'The U.S.S. Old West has capsized, and all the cowboys on board are trying to restore her upright.', 'JH', '1', 'フク', 'おお.う、くつがえ.す、くつがえ.る', NULL, NULL),
('1739', 'smoke', '煙', '<img src=\"E78599.png\" />', 'smoke, hearth fire, old west, soil, dirt, ground', '13', '41', 'In the Old West, they used to light fires in the ground to make smoke signals.', 'JH', '3', 'エン', 'けむ.る、けむり、けむ.い', NULL, NULL),
('174', 'inflammation', '炎', '<img src=\"E7828E.png\" />', 'inflammation, fire, fire2', '8', '8', 'To fight fire with fire would just inflame a situation.', 'JH', '1', 'エン', 'ほのお', NULL, NULL),
('1740', 'south', '南', '<img src=\"E58D97.png\" />', 'south, ten, needle, belt, happiness, ten, needle, stand up, vase, ten2, needle2', '9', '41', 'South of my belt leads to happiness.', '2', '5', 'ナン、ナ', 'みなみ', NULL, NULL),
('1741', 'camphor tree', '楠', '<img src=\"E6A5A0.png\" />', 'camphor tree, tree, wood, south, ten, needle, belt, happiness, ten, needle, stand up, vase, ten2, needle2', '13', '41', 'We traveled to southern Japan just to see a camphor tree. It´s what we came for.', 'Nam', '1', 'ナン、ダン、ゼン、ネン', 'くす、くすのき', NULL, NULL),
('1742', 'offering', '献', '<img src=\"E78CAE.png\" />', 'offering, south, ten, needle, belt, happiness, ten, needle, stand up, vase, chihuahua, dog, large, drop, ten2, needle2', '13', '41', 'A South Korean street vendor is offering chihuahu snacks.', 'JH', '1', 'ケン、コン', 'たてまつ.る', NULL, NULL),
('1743', 'gates', '門', '<img src=\"E99680.png\" />', 'gates', '8', '42', 'Heisig´s stroke order in the 4th edition (and earlier) is wrong, so be careful -- first is the left-most vertical stroke, then draw the rest of the \"sun\" attachment as you would normally. In fact, if you just wrote it out as two suns with elongated sides, you´ll get the stroke order exactly correct.', '2', '2', 'モン', 'かど、と', NULL, NULL),
('1744', 'question', '問', '<img src=\"E5958F.png\" />', 'question, gates, mouth', '11', '42', 'A mouth on the Gates of Hell says \"Answer me these questions three, or thru the gates ye soon will be\".', '3', '4', 'モン', 'と.う、と.い、とん', NULL, NULL),
('1745', 'review', '閲', '<img src=\"E996B2.png\" />', 'review, gates, devil, horns, elder brother, teenager, mouth, human legs', '15', '42', 'A little devil at the gates of hell reviews your record to see if you´re evil enough to get in.', 'JH', '1', 'エツ', 'けみ.する', NULL, NULL),
('1746', 'clique', '閥', '<img src=\"E996A5.png\" />', 'clique, gates, fell, person, fiesta', '14', '42', 'You only get through the gates into that person\'s fiesta if you are in the same clique.', 'JH', '1', 'バツ', '', NULL, NULL),
('1747', 'interval', '間', '<img src=\"E99693.png\" />', 'interval, gates, sun, day', '12', '42', 'The interval between star systems (suns) was too large, so the stargates were created to travel between them.', '2', '5', 'カン、ケン', 'あいだ、ま、あい', NULL, NULL),
('1748', 'pitch dark', '闇', '<img src=\"E99787.png\" />', 'pitch dark, gates, sound, vase, stand up, sun, day', '17', '42', 'I like to think of a horror movie where the protagonists enter a graveyard when suddenly their flashlights go out and it becomes pitch dark, whereupon they hear the sound of the gate creaking shut behind them.', 'JH', '', 'アン、オン', 'やみ、くら.い', NULL, NULL),
('1749', 'simplicity', '簡', '<img src=\"E7B0A1.png\" />', 'simplicity, bamboo, interval, gates, sun, day', '18', '42', '[simplicity; brevity] The ししおどし is a bamboo device for scaring birds from the gates of your garden by clacking against a stone at regular intervals. Its design is simplicity itself. (Inspired by PepeSeco).', '6', '2', 'カン', '', NULL, NULL),
('175', 'anxiety', '煩', '<img src=\"E785A9.png\" />', 'anxiety, fire, head, page, one, ceiling, drop, shellfish, clam, oyster, eye, animal legs, eight', '13', '8', 'An anxiety feels like FIRE in the HEAD.', 'JH', '1', 'ハン、ボン', 'わずら.う、わずら.わす', NULL, NULL),
('1750', 'open', '開', '<img src=\"E9968B.png\" />', 'open, gates, two hands', '12', '42', 'Sure you can squeeze through these gates by kicking them or pushing them with your body, but if you want to get them wide open, you need to do that with both your hands.', '3', '4', 'カイ', 'ひら.く、ひら.き、-びら.き、ひら.ける、あ.く、あ.ける', NULL, NULL),
('1751', 'closed', '閉', '<img src=\"E99689.png\" />', 'closed, gates, genie', '11', '42', 'The gates are too big to be closed by man. Only a genie can. \"Close sesame!\".', '6', '3', 'ヘイ', 'と.じる、と.ざす、し.める、し.まる、た.てる', NULL, NULL),
('1752', 'tower', '閣', '<img src=\"E996A3.png\" />', 'tower, gates, each, walking legs, mouth', '14', '42', 'To keep this distinct from other kanji such as \"watchtower\" and \"pagoda\", I use the mnemonic \"towering tower\". -- In some old 8-bit kung-fu videogame, with a plot similar as Bruce Lee´s last, unfinished movie, the hero must break through a gate at each level of the towering tower, fighting with opponents using various styles of kung-fu until he meets the finale at the topmost level of the \"towering tower\".', '6', '1', 'カク', '', NULL, NULL),
('1753', 'leisure', '閑', '<img src=\"E99691.png\" />', 'leisure, gates, tree, wood', '12', '42', 'Imagine the gates the Garden of Eden, the ultimate land of leisure. You´re not allowed in, but if you peek through you can see trees.', 'JH', '1', 'カン', '', NULL, NULL),
('1754', 'hear', '聞', '<img src=\"E8819E.png\" />', 'hear, gates, ear', '14', '42', 'Press your ear to the gates and see if you can hear what is going on inside.', '2', '5', 'ブン、モン', 'き.く、き.こえる', NULL, NULL),
('1755', 'wet', '潤', '<img src=\"E6BDA4.png\" />', 'wet, water, water droplets, water pistol, intercalate, gates, king, jewel, ball', '15', '42', 'Forgetting about the moat, the king stepped out of his gate and landed in the water. Needless to say he got wet.', 'JH', '1', 'ジュン', 'うるお.う、うるお.す、うる.む', NULL, NULL),
('1756', 'column', '欄', '<img src=\"E6AC84.png\" />', 'column, tree, wood, gates, east, tree, wood, sun, day, tree2, wood2', '20', '42', '[column; handrail; blank; space] I think about oriental (eastern) Torii gates: they have two supporting columns made of wood.', 'JH', '1', 'ラン', 'てすり', NULL, NULL),
('1757', 'fight', '闘', '<img src=\"E99798.png\" />', 'fight, gates, beans, table, one, mouth, glue', '18', '42', 'During the saloon brawl, one guy got glued to a table and was tossed out through the saloon gates. But he really wanted to fight, so he ran back through those gates (with the table still glued to his back) only to be tossed out again. Imagine him repeatedly running in and being tossed back out.', 'JH', '1', 'トウ', 'たたか.う、あらそ.う', NULL, NULL),
('1758', 'godown', '倉', '<img src=\"E58089.png\" />', 'godown, meeting, single gate, umbrella, stable door, mouth', '10', '42', 'A godown is a dockside warehouse. This is actually a meeting of large doors and mouths. The stroke order is the same as door, not gates, just with the top stroke moved down into the now larger door.', '4', '1', 'ソウ', 'くら', NULL, NULL),
('1759', 'genesis', '創', '<img src=\"E589B5.png\" />', 'genesis, godown, meeting, single gate, umbrella, stable door, mouth, sword, sabre, saber', '12', '42', 'Back in the day the people were so excited to get hold of the Sega genesis they looted the godown with sabers.', '6', '1', 'ソウ、ショウ', 'つく.る、はじ.める、きず、けず.しける', NULL, NULL),
('176', 'thin', '淡', '<img src=\"E6B7A1.png\" />', 'thin, water, water droplets, water pistol, inflammation, fire, fire2', '11', '8', 'Drink water and burn twice as many calories as you eat... you´ll definitely get thin. Imagine inside your body, all those calories literally being burned from above and below... THAT´s what it takes to become thin.', 'JH', '1', 'タン', 'あわ.い', NULL, NULL),
('1760', 'un-', '非', '<img src=\"E99D9E.png\" />', 'un-, jail cell, prison bars', '8', '42', 'This looks like a pictogram of 3 fingers from each hand trying to open up a crack in a wall. That´s an un-believable way to escape from prison OR the UN- have a prison in the Hague.', '5', '3', 'ヒ', 'あら.ず', NULL, NULL),
('1761', 'haiku', '俳', '<img src=\"E4BFB3.png\" />', 'haiku, person, un-, jail cell, prison bars', '10', '42', 'I pity the fool/ Who put me in this jail cell/ I pity the fool. (Credit taijuando).', '6', '1', 'ハイ', '', NULL, NULL),
('1762', 'repudiate', '排', '<img src=\"E68E92.png\" />', 'repudiate, finger, fingers, un-, jail cell, prison bars', '11', '42', 'When ordered to go to the jail cell, the defendant gave the judge the finger and said he repudiated all that the legal system stood for if they were going to send an innocent man like him to jail.', 'JH', '1', 'ハイ', '', NULL, NULL),
('1763', 'sad', '悲', '<img src=\"E682B2.png\" />', 'sad, un-, jail cell, prison bars, heart', '12', '42', 'Saddness is like having your heart captured and jailed because of some sad or terrible event, etc. Here the sad heart waits for someone to come and un-lock their jail cell and set them free again.', '3', '3', 'ヒ', 'かな.しい、かな.しむ', NULL, NULL),
('1764', 'guilt', '罪', '<img src=\"E7BDAA.png\" />', 'guilt, eye, cross-eyed, net, un-, jail cell, prison bars', '13', '42', 'Guilty under the eyes of the law, therefore sentenced to jail. [note: ´UNDER the eye of the law´ works in penalty (#833) as well.].', '5', '3', 'ザイ', 'つみ', NULL, NULL),
('1765', 'comrade', '輩', '<img src=\"E8BCA9.png\" />', 'comrade, un-, jail cell, prison bars, car', '15', '42', 'Some man jailed in Russia, is freed by his comrade (from the Communist party perhaps), who crashes into the jail cell with a vehicle.', 'JH', '1', 'ハイ', 'ともがら、 -ばら、 やかい、 やから', NULL, NULL),
