('1832', 'hinge', '枢', '<img src=\"E69EA2.png\" />', 'hinge, tree, wood, ward, box, sheaf', '8', '44', 'Make sure you install the hinge the right way. If it opens treeward (= tree ward), you won\'t be able to get the fence open, make sure it opens houseward.', 'JH', '1', 'スウ、シュ', 'とぼそ、からくり', NULL, NULL),
('1833', 'assault', '殴', '<img src=\"E6AEB4.png\" />', 'assault, ward, box, sheaf, missile, cruise missile, wind, crotch', '8', '44', 'The biggest assault on Japan during WW2 is when the wards in Hiroshima and Nagasaki were wiped out by nuclear missiles.', 'JH', '1', 'オウ', 'なぐ.る', NULL, NULL),
('1834', 'Europe', '欧', '<img src=\"E6ACA7.png\" />', 'europe, ward, box, sheaf, lack, yawn', '8', '44', 'Do japanese consider Europe like just a ward, boring enough to make them yawn?? This kanji is offensive!', 'JH', '2', 'オウ', 'うた.う、は.く', NULL, NULL),
('1835', 'repress', '抑', '<img src=\"E68A91.png\" />', 'repress, finger, fingers, stamp album, box, stamps', '7', '44', 'They would repress dissents by cutting off their fingers and mailing them to relatives in small boxes (of course including stamps for proper postage).', 'JH', '1', 'ヨク', 'おさ.える', NULL, NULL),
('1836', 'faceup', '仰', '<img src=\"E4BBB0.png\" />', 'face up, person, stamp album, box, stamps', '6', '44', 'Mr T with the post package at the post office: ´these stamps don´t stick to the box, foo´ Postguy:´ Try it again but this time with the stamp, face-up.´.', 'JH', '1', 'ギョウ、コウ', 'あお.ぐ、おお.せ、お.っしゃる、おっしゃ.る', NULL, NULL),
('1837', 'welcome', '迎', '<img src=\"E8BF8E.png\" />', 'welcome, stamp album, box, stamps, road', '7', '44', 'Welcome home daddy! Is that box for me? You were on the road a long time! I collected all the stamps from the letters you wrote me　:-) ...　　RTK2:　ゲイ　歓迎　かんげい(welcome).', 'JH', '3', 'ゲイ', 'むか.える', NULL, NULL),
('1838', 'ascend', '登', '<img src=\"E799BB.png\" />', 'ascend, teepee, wigwam, beans, table, one, mouth', '12', '44', 'When an American Indian warrior dies, his body is placed on a TABLE inside a TEEPEE, and a ritualistic ceremony is held to encourage his spirit to ASCEND to that big buffalo hunting ground in the sky.', '3', '3', 'トウ、ト、ドウ、ショウ、チョウ', 'のぼ.る、あ.がる', NULL, NULL),
('1839', 'lucidity', '澄', '<img src=\"E6BE84.png\" />', 'lucidity, water, water droplets, water pistol, ascend, teepee, wigwam, beans, table, one, mouth', '15', '44', 'Scuba divers know that when you ascend in the water, your lucidity increases (For non-divers, the deeper you go, the more you become mentally impaired by nitrogen narcosis, every 50 feet is like drinking one martini). Scuba divers also know that as you ascend in the water, the lucidity of the water improves, too.', 'JH', '1', 'チョウ', 'す.む、す.ます、-す.ます', NULL, NULL),
('184', 'fishing', '漁', '<img src=\"E6BC81.png\" />', 'fishing, water, water droplets, water pistol, fish, bound up, rice field, brains, oven-fire, barbecue', '14', '8', 'You need WATER and FISH for fishing.', '4', '2', 'ギョ、リョウ', 'あさ.る', NULL, NULL),
('1840', 'discharge', '発', '<img src=\"E799BA.png\" />', 'discharge, teepee, wigwam, two, human legs', '9', '44', 'Two pairs of human legs poking out of a teepee: you know there´ll be a discharge soon, be it sexual, violent (husband returns home with a weapon), or dishonourable (soldier caught molesting a native), or perhaps all of the above.', '3', '4', 'ハツ、ホツ', 'た.つ、あば.く、おこ.る、つか.わす、はな.つ', NULL, NULL),
('1841', 'abolish', '廃', '<img src=\"E5BB83.png\" />', 'abolish, cave, dicharge, teepee, wigwam, two, human legs', '12', '44', 'Slaves have been discharged from the caves where they were kept thanks to the abolition of slavery.', 'JH', '1', 'ハイ', 'すた.れる、すた.る', NULL, NULL),
('1842', 'colleague', '僚', '<img src=\"E5839A.png\" />', 'colleague, person, pup tent, large, St. Bernard, sun, day, small, little', '14', '44', 'A colleague implies someone that you share work with, such as in your company or profession, etc. Here your colleague helps you to erect your pup tent during a company outing. Note: Heisig\'s warning to keep this distinct from other similiar kanji such as companion (#19), friend (#704), consort (#1203) and comrade (#1637). That is why I chose to have the person element pictured as someone (the colleague in this case) helping with the work of building the pup tent.', 'JH', '1', 'リョウ', '', NULL, NULL),
('1843', 'obvious', '瞭', '<img src=\"E79EAD.png\" />', 'obvious, eye, pup tent, large, St. Bernard, sun, day, small, little', '17', '44', 'Open your eyes, it\'s obvious that not all of us can fit into that small puptent!', 'JH', '1', 'リョウ', 'あきらか', NULL, NULL),
('1844', 'dormitory', '寮', '<img src=\"E5AFAE.png\" />', 'dormitory, house, pup tent, large, St. Bernard, sun, day, small, little', '15', '44', 'A dormitory is right in the middle between living in a house and living in a pup tent.', 'JH', '1', 'リョウ', '', NULL, NULL),
('1845', 'heal', '療', '<img src=\"E79982.png\" />', 'heal, sickness, hospital, pup tent, large, St. Bernard, sun, day, small, little', '17', '44', 'On the battlefield, the only place to heal from your sickness is inside the medic\'s pup tent. Think of M.A.S.H.', 'JH', '2', 'リョウ', '', NULL, NULL),
('1846', 'carve', '彫', '<img src=\"E5BDAB.png\" />', 'carve, circumference, running track, glass hood, earthenware jar, lidded crock, soil, dirt, ground, mouth, shape', '11', '45', 'A lathe is used to carve a shape with circumference into wood or metal.', 'JH', '1', 'チョウ', 'ほ.る、-ぼ.り', NULL, NULL),
('1847', 'shape', '形', '<img src=\"E5BDA2.png\" />', 'shape, two hands, shape', '7', '45', 'Everyone in the kindergarten came up with fun and interesting shapes made out of Play-Doh, except for the kid with the amputated arm. Seems like you really need both hands.', '2', '3', 'ケイ、ギョウ', 'かた、-がた、かたち、なり', NULL, NULL),
('1848', 'shadow', '影', '<img src=\"E5BDB1.png\" />', 'shadow, scenery, sun, day, capital, tall, top hat, mouth, small, little, shape', '15', '45', 'The sun over the capital cast a shadow with the same shape.', 'JH', '1', 'エイ', 'かげ', NULL, NULL),
('1849', 'cedar', '杉', '<img src=\"E69D89.png\" />', 'cedar, tree, wood, shape', '7', '45', 'Cedar is an evergreen tree that keeps its SHAPE all year long. That is, it doesn´t loose its needles/leaves in the winter.', 'JH', '1', 'サン', 'すぎ', NULL, NULL),
('185', 'ri', '里', '<img src=\"E9878C.png\" />', 'ri, computer, rice field, brains, soil, dirt, ground', '7', '9', 'The ri is a Japanese way of measuring the area of the GROUND underneath a RICE FIELD.', '2', '', 'リ', 'さと', NULL, NULL),
('1850', 'coloring', '彩', '<img src=\"E5BDA9.png\" />', 'coloring, claw, vulture, grab, tree, wood, shape', '11', '45', 'In Sydney we occasionally get exotic birds. You first notice a colouring in a tree. You look more carefully and you make out the shape of a bird (here represented by its claws).', 'JH', '1', 'サイ', 'いろど.る', NULL, NULL),
