('1855', 'swell', '膨', '<img src=\"E886A8.png\" />', 'swell, moon, month, flesh, part of the body, drum, samurai, beans, table, one, mouth, shape', '16', '45', 'This kanji does not mean swell as in a inflammation. There is a different kanji for that meaning (腫れる). This kanji means swell as in, a tire swelling/expanding, your income swelling/expanding, dough swelling/expanding, etc. Johnskb\'s story is best b/c it does not involve swelling in the sense of inflammation, just general expansion of the stomach. STORY: \"If a PART OF your BODY begins to SWELL/EXPAND and resembles the SHAPE of a bass DRUM, you’re either pregnant or in desperate need of a diet.\".', 'JH', '1', 'ボウ', 'ふく.らむ、ふく.れる', NULL, NULL),
('1856', 'visit', '参', '<img src=\"E58F82.png\" />', 'nonplussed, visit, elbow, large, St. Bernard, shape', '8', '45', 'I´m going to visit my grandpa in the hospital. He broke his elbow, and it became really big and contorted into a weird shape. I hope he will be all right!', '4', '3', 'サン、シン', 'まい.る、まい-、まじわる、みつ', NULL, NULL),
('1857', 'wretched', '惨', '<img src=\"E683A8.png\" />', 'wretched, Freud, state of mind, nonplussed, visit, elbow, large, St. Bernard, shape', '11', '45', 'Whenever I have to visit the relatives... that puts me in one hell of a wretched state of mind.', 'JH', '1', 'サン、ザン', 'みじ.め、いた.む、むご.い', NULL, NULL),
('1858', 'discipline', '修', '<img src=\"E4BFAE.png\" />', 'discipline, person, stick, fred astaire, taskmaster, shape', '10', '45', 'Mr. T is a harsh taskmaster who will discipline you (beat you into shape) with his walking stick.', '5', '1', 'シュウ、シュ', 'おさ.める、おさ.まる', NULL, NULL),
('1859', 'rare', '珍', '<img src=\"E78F8D.png\" />', 'rare, king, jewel, ball, parasol, umbrella, shape', '9', '45', 'It\'s rare to see the king carrying his own parasol - typically he gets one of his attendants to do it for him (thanks to Katsuo for umbrella + shape = parasol and to Peppi for the story idea).', 'JH', '2', 'チン', 'めずら.しい、たから', NULL, NULL),
('186', 'black', '黒', '<img src=\"E9BB92.png\" />', 'black, computer, oven-fire, barbecue', '11', '9', 'If you burn the GROUND of a RICE FIELD with FIRE, eventually it will turn black.', '2', '4', 'コク', 'くろ、くろ.ずむ、くろ.い', NULL, NULL),
('1860', 'checkup', '診', '<img src=\"E8A8BA.png\" />', 'check up, say, words, keitai, mouth, parasol, umbrella, shape', '12', '45', 'At my last check-up, the doctor said to me: \"Start carrying a parasol, or you might get skin cancer. You\'ve been tanning too much!\" [Umbrella over shape = parasol].', 'JH', '1', 'シン', 'み.る', NULL, NULL),
('1861', 'sentence', '文', '<img src=\"E69687.png\" />', 'sentence, plaid, kilt, Billy Connolly', '4', '45', 'A twist on greenapple: The teacher puts a tophat on all pupils with gramatically correct sentences, while the rest are left with a big red X on their homework.', '1', '4', 'ブン、モン', 'ふみ、あや', NULL, NULL),
