('1873', 'medicine', '薬', '<img src=\"E896AC.png\" />', 'medicine, flowers, music, white, dove, sparkler, tree, wood', '16', '45', 'New-age medicine involves using things like music and flowers (aromatherapy) as treatment.', '3', '3', 'ヤク', 'くすり', NULL, NULL),
('1874', 'ratio', '率', '<img src=\"E78E87.png\" />', 'ratio, mysterious, question mark, top hat, cocoon, sparkler, ten, needle', '11', '45', 'It´s quite mysterious how each sparkler gives of sparkles at a precise ratio of ten to one. Physicists have been studying this effect for decades, known as the Sparkler Effect, and using it to explain why stars look like sparklers in the night sky.', '5', '1', 'ソツ、リツ、シュツ', 'ひき.いる', NULL, NULL),
('1875', 'astringent', '渋', '<img src=\"E6B88B.png\" />', 'astringent, water, water droplets, water pistol, stop, footprint, sparkler', '11', '45', 'I think that Heisig meant this as the \"slightly bitter but fresh\" meaning that it can have to describe foods like lemons (しぶい). So imagine a guy trying a cocktail (water), feeling like he´s been kicked in the face (footprint) and sparks are flying from his tongue. ´How did it taste?´. ´Hmm, yes, slightly bitter, but fresh\".', 'JH', '1', 'ジュウ、シュウ', 'しぶ、しぶ.い、しぶ.る', NULL, NULL),
('1876', 'vicarious', '摂', '<img src=\"E69182.png\" />', 'vicarious, finger, fingers, ear, sparkler', '13', '45', 'Now that I´m a responsible adult, I have to get my vicarious thrills from watching stupid people put sparklers up to their ears and burn their fingers.', 'JH', '1', 'セツ、ショウ', 'おさ.める、かね.る、と.る', NULL, NULL),
('1877', 'center', '央', '<img src=\"E5A4AE.png\" />', 'center, large, St. Bernard, box body', '5', '45', 'Youve got the st bernard dead centre in your sights (the box).', '3', '2', 'オウ', '', NULL, NULL),
