('2148', 'void', '虚', '<img src=\"E8999A.png\" />', 'void, tiger, row', '11', '54', 'In Japanese folklore there is no hell, but there is the void. There, a row of tigers waits in the blackness to devour those souls who have failed in their spiritual life.', 'JH', '1', 'キョ、コ', 'むな.しい、うつ.ろ', NULL, NULL),
('2149', 'frolic', '戯', '<img src=\"E688AF.png\" />', 'frolic, void, tiger, row, fiesta', '15', '54', 'This is a story about the end of the universe. The universe is turning into a featureless void. There´s nothing we can do about it except for throw a fiesta and frolic a little bit before it´s all over.', 'JH', '1', 'ギ、ゲ', 'たわむ.れる、ざ.れる、じゃ.れる', NULL, NULL),
('215', 'apricot', '杏', '<img src=\"E69D8F.png\" />', 'apricot, tree, wood, mouth', '7', '10', 'From the tree straight into the mouth is the best way to eat an APRICOT!', 'Nam', '1', 'キョウ、アン、コウ', 'あんず', NULL, NULL),
('2150', 'uneasiness', '虞', '<img src=\"E8999E.png\" />', 'uneasiness, tiger, give, mouth, chair, tool', '13', '54', 'I feel a sense of uneasiness about giving this HUGE tiger a steak.', 'JH', '1', 'グ', 'おそれ、おもんぱか.る、はか.る、うれ.える、あざむ.く、あやま.る、のぞ.む、たの.しむ', NULL, NULL),
('2151', 'prudence', '慮', '<img src=\"E685AE.png\" />', 'prudence, tiger, think, rice field, brains, heart', '15', '54', 'Real meaning: \"to ponder\". You have to think with prudence (ponder carefully) about approaching a tiger, as is evident from 虎.', 'JH', '1', 'リョ', 'おもんぱく.る、おもんぱか.る', NULL, NULL),
('2152', 'drama', '劇', '<img src=\"E58A87.png\" />', 'drama, tiger, sow, pig, sword, sabre, saber', '15', '54', 'There would be a lot of drama if a tiger tried to eat a sow but then the sow attacked it with a saber.', '6', '2', 'ゲキ', '', NULL, NULL),
('2153', 'tyrannize', '虐', '<img src=\"E89990.png\" />', 'tyrannize, tiger, one, box', '9', '54', 'Here we see the evil tyrannizing tiger. What is on his chest? A giant E, for EVIL, of course.', 'JH', '1', 'ギャク', 'しいた.げる', NULL, NULL),
('2154', 'deer', '鹿', '<img src=\"E9B9BF.png\" />', 'deer, cave, antlers, compare, spoon, sitting on the ground, spoon2, sitting on the ground2', '11', '54', 'Bambi wanders into a cave and sees a side order of salad and 2 spoons...but what´s the main course?', 'JH', '1', 'ロク', 'しか、か', NULL, NULL),
('2155', 'foot of a mountain', '麓', '<img src=\"E9BA93.png\" />', 'foot of a mountain, grove, tree, wood, deer, cave, antlers, compare, spoon, sitting on the ground, spoon2, sitting on the ground2', '19', '54', 'Many deer can be found in the grove at the foot of a mountain.', 'JH', '', 'ロク', 'ふもと', NULL, NULL),
('2156', 'recommend', '薦', '<img src=\"E896A6.png\" />', 'recommend, flowers, deer, cave, antlers, slingshot, catapult, tail feathers', '16', '54', 'Customer in restaurant asks you (waiter) what you recommend: \"I recommend ze deer or ze \'eadless chicken. And I recommend you garnish it wiz some flowers.\" (let last six strokes = headless chicken).', 'JH', '1', 'セン', 'すす.める', NULL, NULL),
('2157', 'jubilation', '慶', '<img src=\"E685B6.png\" />', 'jubilation, deer, cave, antlers, crown, heart, walking legs', '15', '54', 'The hunter experienced jubilation when the deer with melancholy walked up to him and said, \"just shoot me, whats the point in running. Everyone dies someday...\"', 'JH', '1', 'ケイ', 'よろこ.び', NULL, NULL),
('2158', 'lovely', '麗', '<img src=\"E9BA97.png\" />', 'lovely, one, ceiling, mediocre, deer, cave, antlers, compare, ceiling2, mediocre2, compare2', '19', '54', 'The anthropologist made an exact deer painting from the cave ceiling on the ceiling of his house. Too bad they´re both mediocre. All his wife could say was, \"How...lovely.\".', 'JH', '1', 'レイ', 'うるわ.しい、うら.らか', NULL, NULL),
('2159', 'bear', '熊', '<img src=\"E7868A.png\" />', 'bear, ability, elbow, moon, month, flesh, part of the body, spoon, sitting on the ground, oven-fire, barbecue, spoon2, sitting on the ground2', '14', '54', 'Most don´t know it, but bears have the ability to walk on fire. They´re invincible creatures!', 'JH', '1', 'ユウ', 'くま', NULL, NULL),
('216', 'paulownia', '桐', '<img src=\"E6A190.png\" />', 'paulownia, tree, wood, same, monks, hood, one, mouth', '10', '10', 'In Japan, a paulownia (きり）is known as the \"princess tree\". It was once a traditional TREE planted at the SAME time as the birth of a daughter. It would grow fast enough that, at the time of her wedding, it could be used to make a dresser as a wedding present for her.', 'Nam', '1', 'トウ、ドウ', 'きり', NULL, NULL),
('2160', 'ability', '能', '<img src=\"E883BD.png\" />', 'ability, elbow, moon, month, flesh, part of the body, spoon, sitting on the ground, spoon2, sitting on the ground2', '10', '54', 'This man may have the dis-ability of no flesh below the elbows, but he can eat with 2 spoons, on in each foot.', '5', '3', 'ノウ', 'よ.く', NULL, NULL),
('2161', 'attitude', '態', '<img src=\"E6858B.png\" />', 'attitude, ability, elbow, moon, month, flesh, part of the body, spoon, sitting on the ground, heart, spoon2, sitting on the ground2', '14', '54', 'This guy has an attitude problem – lots of ability, but his heart´s not in it.', '5', '1', 'タイ', 'わざ.と', NULL, NULL),
('2162', 'sign of the tiger', '寅', '<img src=\"E5AF85.png\" />', 'sign of the tiger, house, caterpillar, one, ceiling, sprout, shoot, animal legs, eight', '11', '55', 'I don\'t know why but when I read sign of the tiger I get the \"eye of the tiger song\" stuck in my head. So I see rocky training in his house. Hes hitting the ceiling (no punching bag) eating brussel sprouts to keep in good health and running with only the animal legs his dog.', 'Nam', '1', 'イン', 'とら', NULL, NULL),
('2163', 'performance', '演', '<img src=\"E6BC94.png\" />', 'performance, water, water droplets, water pistol, sign of the tiger, house, caterpillar, one, ceiling, sprout, shoot, animal legs, eight', '14', '55', 'Studies have shown that Rocky\'s PERFORMANCE increases if he downs WATER mixed with gatorade while in a match.', '5', '3', 'エン', '', NULL, NULL),
('2164', 'sign of the dragon', '辰', '<img src=\"E8BEB0.png\" />', 'sign of the dragon, cliff, two, hairpin, safety-pin', '7', '55', 'I\'m going with the Mortal Kombat Symbol, as it\'s the closest thing to a sign of the dragon I know. In that game, there\'s a place called the pit to which you can throw your opponent on round two, but only with a hairpin punch.', 'Nam', '1', 'シン、ジン', 'たつ', NULL, NULL),
('2165', 'embarrass', '辱', '<img src=\"E8BEB1.png\" />', 'embarrass, sign of the dragon, cliff, two, hairpin, safety-pin, glue', '10', '55', 'If you get too close to a fire-breathing dragon, your skin can turn red from the burn. When someone is embarrassed, it\'s as though they have this sign of the dragon stuck to their face.', 'JH', '1', 'ジョク', 'はずかし.める', NULL, NULL),
('2166', 'quake', '震', '<img src=\"E99C87.png\" />', 'quake, rain, weather, sign of the dragon, cliff, two, hairpin, safety-pin', '15', '55', 'An earthquake is a sign that a dragon is awakening after a heavy rain... It is angry for having been woken up and it makes the earth thunder and quake above it.', 'JH', '2', 'シン', 'ふる.う、ふる.える', NULL, NULL),
('2167', 'shake', '振', '<img src=\"E68CAF.png\" />', 'shake, finger, fingers, sign of the dragon, cliff, two, hairpin, safety-pin', '10', '55', 'Your mother shakes herfinger violently - no, no, no - no Mortal Kombat today!', 'JH', '1', 'シン', 'ふ.る、ぶ.る、ふ.り、-ぶ.り、ふ.るう', NULL, NULL),
('2168', 'with child', '娠', '<img src=\"E5A8A0.png\" />', 'with child, woman, sign of the dragon, cliff, two, hairpin, safety-pin', '10', '55', 'A woman who is with child can\'t be sacrificed to the dragon; virgins only need apply.', 'JH', '1', 'シン', '', NULL, NULL),
('2169', 'lips', '唇', '<img src=\"E59487.png\" />', 'lips, sign of the dragon, cliff, two, hairpin, safety-pin, mouth', '10', '55', 'Sign of the Dragon + Mouth: Lips need chapstick during the wintertime so they don\'t look like the sign of the dragon who kissed you on the mouth.', 'JH', '1', 'シン', 'くちびる', NULL, NULL),
('217', 'plant', '植', '<img src=\"E6A48D.png\" />', 'plant, tree, wood, straightaway, ten, needle, eye, fishhook', '12', '10', 'Plants don´t become trees straightaway.', '3', '2', 'ショク', 'う.える、う.わる', NULL, NULL);
INSERT INTO `kanjis` (`ID_Kanji`, `K_Keyword`, `K_Kanji`, `K_StrokeDiagram`, `K_Constituent`, `K_StrokeCount`, `K_LessonNo`, `K_Story`, `K_JouYou`, `K_JLPT`, `K_OnYomi`, `K_KunYomi`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
('2170', 'agriculture', '農', '<img src=\"E8BEB2.png\" />', 'agriculture, bend, sign of the dragon, cliff, two, hairpin, safety-pin', '13', '55', 'Imagine if you could bend a dragon to your will. Helpful in war, yes, but also a boon for agriculture. The dragon could use its sharp claws to plough the ground, and use its firey breath to clear the land. But first you\'d have to bend the dragon to your will -- not an easy task.', '3', '2', 'ノウ', '', NULL, NULL),
('2171', 'concentrated', '濃', '<img src=\"E6BF83.png\" />', 'concentrated, water, water droplets, water pistol, agriculture, bend, sign of the dragon, cliff, two, hairpin, safety-pin', '16', '55', 'The agriculture of Florida is concentrated on making concentrated orange juice. Just add water! Imagine a can of FCOJ, dumping it into a pitcher and adding water.', 'JH', '2', 'ノウ', 'こ.い', NULL, NULL),
('2172', 'send off', '送', '<img src=\"E98081.png\" />', 'escort, send off, golden calf, horns, heavens, road', '9', '55', 'The St Bernard with devilish animal horns must be non other than Cerberus, guard dog of the netherworld. In this frame Cerberus is seen along the road to hell, escorting those who have been sent off to join Hades in his realm.', '3', '4', 'ソウ', 'おく.る', NULL, NULL),
('2173', 'connection', '関', '<img src=\"E996A2.png\" />', 'connection, gates, golden calf, horns, heavens', '14', '55', 'At the airport, the woolly mammoth was too big. When he tried to go through his flight\'s gate he got stuck and missed his connecting flight.', '4', '3', 'カン', 'せき、-ぜき、かか.わる、からくり、かんぬき', NULL, NULL),
('2174', 'blossom', '咲', '<img src=\"E592B2.png\" />', 'blossom, mouth, golden calf, horns, heavens', '9', '55', 'The mouth of the wooly mammoth was so big and furry that plants would actually grow and blossom there.', 'JH', '2', 'ショウ', 'さ.く、-ざき', NULL, NULL),
('2175', 'ghost', '鬼', '<img src=\"E9ACBC.png\" />', 'ghost, oni, drop, brains, rice field, human legs, elbow', '10', '55', '鬼(おに) is not a ghost. An ogre or a troll would be a more fitting translation. Such a thing has but a drop of brains and uses its legs and elbows as deadly weapons (a concept which should be familiar from the license (#765) to kill). I\'ll use \"ogre\" for this.', 'JH', '1', 'キ', 'おに、おに-', NULL, NULL),
('2176', 'ugly', '醜', '<img src=\"E9869C.png\" />', 'ugly, whiskey bottle, ghost, oni, drop, brains, rice field, human legs, elbow', '17', '55', 'The ugly oni can´t get a date so he drinks sake by himself at the bar.', 'JH', '1', 'シュウ', 'みにく.い、しこ', NULL, NULL),
('2177', 'soul', '魂', '<img src=\"E9AD82.png\" />', 'soul, rising cloud, two, elbow, wall, ghost, oni, drop, brains, rice field, human legs, elbow, elbow2', '14', '55', 'When you die, your SOUL either goes to the RISING CLOUDS (heaven) or to the ONI (hell, the devil).', 'JH', '1', 'コン', 'たましい、たま', NULL, NULL),
('2178', 'witch', '魔', '<img src=\"E9AD94.png\" />', 'witch, hemp, cliff, grove, tree, wood, ghost, oni, drop, brains, rice field, human legs, elbow, tree2, wood2', '21', '55', 'This modern version of the witch lives in some hippie community. She smokes a lot of hemp, and spends the day talking to ghosts, which not surprisingly appears only to her.', 'JH', '1', 'マ', '', NULL, NULL),
('2179', 'fascination', '魅', '<img src=\"E9AD85.png\" />', 'fascination, ghost, oni, drop, brains, rice field, human legs, elbow, not yet, one, tree, wood', '15', '55', 'Ghosts have not yet left the world, they must still have a deep fascination with their past life on Earth.', 'JH', '1', 'ミ', '', NULL, NULL),
('218', 'chair', '椅', '<img src=\"E6A485.png\" />', 'chair, tree, wood, strange, large, St. Bernard, street, nail, spike, mouth', '12', '10', 'To the Japanese, the first time they saw a chair, it looked like a strange use of wood! Probably why they still like to sit on the floor...', 'JH', '', 'イ', '', NULL, NULL),
('2180', 'clod', '塊', '<img src=\"E5A18A.png\" />', 'clod, soil, dirt, ground, ghost, oni, drop, brains, rice field, human legs, elbow', '13', '55', 'Without any weapons, our only defense was to throw clods of dirt at the advancing oni horde. (Adapted from dingomick because zombie was used as a primitive for drag+rag).', 'JH', '1', 'カイ、ケ', 'かたまり、つちくれ', NULL, NULL),
('2181', 'attack', '襲', '<img src=\"E8A5B2.png\" />', 'attack, old dragon, vase, stand up, moon, month, flesh, part of the body, slingshot, catapult, snake, self, three, cloth, clothes, clothing, garment, dragon*', '22', '55', 'The top 16 strokes are the chinese radical for \"dragon\". Joining up both meanings of the radical we can name the top part of this kanji \"imperial dragon\". Two-headed snakes do exist as biological curiosities, and they look a bit like a slingshot (with the heads splitting at a junction). Our imperial dragon here, the pet of a Chinese emperor, is a rare \"three-headed slingshot-snake\" kept in a vase and fed with meat. When the emperor attacked neighbours, his army wore the imperial dragon garment.', 'JH', '1', 'シュウ', 'おそ.う、かさ.ね', NULL, NULL),
('2182', 'upbraid', '嚇', '<img src=\"E59A87.png\" />', 'menacing, upbraid, mouth, incandescent, red, red2', '17', '56', 'To upbraid someone, you criticize them in a menacing way. In other words, you jaw at them with your MOUTH until both sides of their face turn RED (hence the double-red).', 'JH', '1', 'カク', 'おど.かす', NULL, NULL),
('2183', 'majestic plural', '朕', '<img src=\"E69C95.png\" />', 'majestic plural, moon, month, flesh, part of the body, golden calf, horns, heavens', '10', '56', 'The queen is not happy. \"We (majestic plural) are not amused that the hunger for the flesh of the wooly mammoth has caused it\'s extinction. Poor Charles is particularly upset.', 'JH', '1', 'チン', '', NULL, NULL),
('2184', 'atmosphere', '雰', '<img src=\"E99BB0.png\" />', 'atmosphere, rain, weather, part', '12', '56', 'The part of the sky that is responsible for weather and rain is known as the atmosphere. It only occupies part of the sky though.', 'JH', '1', 'フン', '', NULL, NULL),
('2185', 'item', '箇', '<img src=\"E7AE87.png\" />', 'item, bamboo, harden, pent in, old, tombstone, gravestone, church, ten, needle, mouth', '14', '56', 'Dragon Quest - You find a hardened bamboo stick, perfect for a weapon, but you can´t pick it up because your items are full.', 'JH', '1', 'カ、コ', '', NULL, NULL),
('2186', 'tempering', '錬', '<img src=\"E98CAC.png\" />', 'tempering, metal, gold, east, tree, wood, sun, day', '16', '56', 'In the East, especially Japan ...there are masters of tempering metal to great strength....on the Spring of Trivia show in Japan I saw how a Japanese sword ...actually split flying bullets...all because of special Eastern tempering techniques.', 'JH', '1', 'レン', 'ね.る', NULL, NULL),
('2187', 'abide by', '遵', '<img src=\"E981B5.png\" />', 'abide by, revered, Mother Teresa, chieftain, Molotov cocktail, animal horns, whiskey bottle, glue, road', '15', '56', 'You must abide by the revered rules of the road! No devil´s brew and stay glued to your lane in the road!', 'JH', '1', 'ジュン', '', NULL, NULL),
('2188', 'quit', '罷', '<img src=\"E7BDB7.png\" />', 'quit, eye, cross-eyed, net, ability, elbow, moon, month, flesh, part of the body, spoon, sitting on the ground, spoon2, sitting on the ground2', '15', '56', 'Hey, screw you! Don´t you look down on me! I have the ability to quit anytime I want!', 'JH', '1', 'ヒ', 'まか.り-、や.める', NULL, NULL),
('2189', 'barracks', '屯', '<img src=\"E5B1AF.png\" />', 'barracks, earthworm, drop, shovel, fishhook', '4', '56', 'The game characters from Worms sleep in their barracks at night.', 'JH', '1', 'トン', '', NULL, NULL),
('219', 'wither', '枯', '<img src=\"E69EAF.png\" />', 'wither, tree, wood, old, tombstone, gravestone, church, ten, needle, mouth', '9', '10', 'A tree withers away as it gets old.', 'JH', '2', 'コ', 'か.れる、か.らす', NULL, NULL),
('2190', 'moreover', '且', '<img src=\"E4B894.png\" />', 'moreover, shelf, my bookshelves', '5', '56', 'Moreover is a literary term to shelve what you had just been talking about, to come back to it later.', 'JH', '1', 'ショ、ソ、ショウ', 'か.つ', NULL, NULL),
('2191', 'seaweed', '藻', '<img src=\"E897BB.png\" />', 'seaweed, flowers, water, water droplets, water pistol, furniture, goods, mouth, tree, wood, mouth3', '19', '56', 'Goods + wood = paper. You know how nori, ie: seaweed, comes in sheets for putting in your ramen or for your sushi? Well that\'s because it\'s water paper! Seaweed is also a sea flower of sorts, so it all just works out.', 'JH', '1', 'ソウ', 'も', NULL, NULL),
('2192', 'slave', '隷', '<img src=\"E99AB7.png\" />', 'slave, samurai, altar, show, two, small, sieve, rake, grains of rice', '16', '56', 'In an attempt to free them from being slaves to their desires, the samurai stands behind the altar likening a clear mind to a sieve that lets only the purest thoughts through.', 'JH', '1', 'レイ', 'したが.う、しもべ', NULL, NULL),
('2193', 'healing', '癒', '<img src=\"E79992.png\" />', 'healing, sickness, hospital, in the nick of time, meeting of butchers, moon, month, flesh, part of the body, sword, sabre, saber, heart', '18', '56', '(Think rpg!) We were in dire need of healing. Our party was fighting the cavemen, but we didn\'t fare too well. It was more like a butcher\'s meeting than a fight... just as they were about to pierce my heart, luckily a priest came along and used his healing spell in the nick of time (#2433).', 'JH', '1', 'ユ', 'い.える、いや.す', NULL, NULL),
('2194', 'imperial seal', '璽', '<img src=\"E792BD.png\" />', 'imperial seal, let it be, noren, one, ceiling, eight, towel, stitching, patchwork quilt, jewel, earring', '19', '56', 'The imperial seal is usually an impressive mark made with a jewel. However when the letter arrives it has been raining on it and you see that the drops of rain have been transformed into little x’s where some animal legs have run over it.', 'JH', '', 'ジ', '', NULL, NULL),
('2195', 'lagoon', '潟', '<img src=\"E6BD9F.png\" />', 'lagoon, water, water droplets, water pistol, mortar, tail feathers', '15', '56', 'Right part: mortar bound up over oven fire, comprising boiling cauldron. Lagoon is a shallow pond, thus easily warmed by sun, large-scale equivalent of a boiling cauldron.', 'JH', '1', 'セキ', 'かた、-がた', NULL, NULL),
('2196', 'cinnabar', '丹', '<img src=\"E4B8B9.png\" />', 'rust colored, cinnabar, ship´s funnel', '4', '56', 'How about a rusty cinnabar colored dilapidated boat, found abandoned somewhere. The smoke-stack and the keel have fallen off...', 'JH', '1', 'タン', 'に', NULL, NULL),
('2197', 'sign of the cow', '丑', '<img src=\"E4B891.png\" />', 'sign of the cow, dagger, two', '5', '56', 'Pictograph of a stanchion, which includes two vertical posts to restrain cows so they can be milked, with a horizontal stroke showing the number of cows per stanchion: one. A stanchion is a great symbol for the SIGN OF THE COW, since modern, domesticated cows are often stanchioned in barns.', 'Nam', '1', 'チュウ', 'うし', NULL, NULL),
('2198', 'humiliate', '羞', '<img src=\"E7BE9E.png\" />', '', '11', '56', 'The sheep had his coat shaven in the winter and a sign of th cow branded on him. How humiliating.', 'JH', '', 'シュウ', 'すすめ.る、 はじ.る、 は.ずかしい', NULL, NULL),
('2199', 'sign of the hare', '卯', '<img src=\"E58DAF.png\" />', 'sign of the hare, blown eggs', '5', '56', 'You know how missing childrens´ pictures often appear on milk cartons? Well here we have a missing hare. His concerned family is having his picture printed on the backs of receipts and even on stamps. So far, however, there has been no SIGN OF THE HARE.', 'Nam', '1', 'ボウ、モウ', 'う', NULL, NULL),
('22', 'sparkle', '晶', '<img src=\"E699B6.png\" />', 'sparkle, day, sun, day3, sun3', '12', '2', 'A diamond sparkles as brightly as three suns.', 'JH', '1', 'ショウ', '', NULL, NULL),
('220', 'crude', '朴', '<img src=\"E69CB4.png\" />', 'crude, tree, wood, magic wand, augury', '6', '10', 'Wooden wands are the crudest. They are nothng compared to their carbon fibre equivilents.', 'JH', '1', 'ボク', 'ほう、ほお、えのき', NULL, NULL),
('2200', 'sign of the snake', '巳', '<img src=\"E5B7B3.png\" />', 'sign of the snake, mosaic with bit missing', '3', '56', 'The 巳nd! Thanks all.', 'Nam', '1', 'シ', 'み', NULL, NULL),
('221', 'town', '村', '<img src=\"E69D91.png\" />', 'town, tree, wood, measure, glue', '7', '10', 'If you´ve ever played an old 8 bit or 16 bit RPG, like Dragon Warrior or Final Fantasy or Inindou, you´ll remember that every town was all bordered off by a line of trees with no space in between to get out through. Imagine that the trees were glued together so you could only exit town through the main or side gates, (so you couldn´t escape the important scripted scenes.).', '1', '2', 'ソン', 'むら', NULL, NULL),
('222', 'inter-', '相', '<img src=\"E79BB8.png\" />', 'inter-, tree, wood, eye', '9', '10', 'The prime minister is having inter-course behind that tree! All you can see are his eyes poking out from the righthand-side of the tree.', '3', '3', 'ソウ、ショウ', 'あい-', NULL, NULL),
('223', 'desk', '机', '<img src=\"E69CBA.png\" />', 'desk, tree, wood, wind', '6', '10', 'My wooden desk is so messy, it looks like a strong wind blew my things all over it.', '6', '2', 'キ', 'つくえ', NULL, NULL),
('224', 'book', '本', '<img src=\"E69CAC.png\" />', 'book, tree, wood, one', '5', '10', 'The origin of a book is paper made out of TREEs. ONE tree can make many books.', '1', '5', 'ホン', 'もと', NULL, NULL),
('225', 'tag', '札', '<img src=\"E69CAD.png\" />', 'tag, tree, wood, fishhook', '5', '10', 'Botanists like to identify TREEs by HOOKing tags on them.', '4', '2', 'サツ', 'ふだ', NULL, NULL),
('226', 'calendar', '暦', '<img src=\"E69AA6.png\" />', 'calendar, cliff, grove, tree, wood, sun, day, tree2, wood2', '14', '10', 'Years-Months-Days: It takes many years for a cliff to form or erode. A tree takes many months to grow. But days pass by regularly - so in this way, we see the movement of time such as with a CALENDAR.', 'JH', '1', 'レキ', 'こよみ、りゃく', NULL, NULL),
('227', 'plan', '案', '<img src=\"E6A188.png\" />', 'plan, relax, house, woman, tree, wood', '10', '10', 'I plan to RELAX on top of that TREE.', '4', '1', 'アン', 'つくえ', NULL, NULL),
('228', 'parch', '燥', '<img src=\"E787A5.png\" />', 'parch, fire, furniture, wooden goods, mouth, tree, wood, mouth3', '17', '10', 'Tip: goods + wood/tree : This combination of primitives appears four times in Heisig, so it´s worthwhile giving it a name. I suggest \"furniture\" (a common type of wooden goods). REF: parch (FRAME 215) , maneuver (#671), winding (#1369), seaweed (#2035). Story: It´s been so parched recently that your furniture suddenly catches fire.', 'JH', '2', 'ソウ', 'はしゃ.ぐ', NULL, NULL),
