('301', 'escape', '逃', '<img src=\"E98083.png\" />', 'escape, turtle, portent, road', '9', '13', 'I used my pants to make a rope, which I then used to escape from prison; hence the naked, hairy legs running along the road!', 'JH', '3', 'トウ', 'に.げる、に.がす、のが.す、のが.れる', NULL, NULL),
('302', 'environs', '辺', '<img src=\"E8BEBA.png\" />', 'environs, dagger, sword, road', '5', '13', 'Caution: this kanji doesn´t mean environment; it means \"environs; boundary; border; vicinity\". To separate the environs, create the border by placing daggers on the road.', '4', '2', 'ヘン', 'あた.り、ほと.り、-べ', NULL, NULL),
('303', 'patrol', '巡', '<img src=\"E5B7A1.png\" />', 'patrol, deluge, stream, flood, road', '6', '13', 'The cops don´t PATROL anymore - they just flood the road.', 'JH', '1', 'ジュン', 'めぐ.る、めぐ.り', NULL, NULL),
('304', 'car', '車', '<img src=\"E8BB8A.png\" />', 'car, sun, ten, needle', '7', '13', 'My car is so fast it can go through ten rice fields in ten minutes.', '1', '5', 'シャ', 'くるま', NULL, NULL),
('305', 'take along', '連', '<img src=\"E980A3.png\" />', 'take along, car, road', '10', '13', 'When you put your car on the road you should always take along a few friends. Don´t confuse with carry (#303).', '4', '3', 'レン', 'つら.なる、つら.ねる、つ.れる、-づ.れ', NULL, NULL),
('306', 'rut', '軌', '<img src=\"E8BB8C.png\" />', 'rut, car, nine, baseball', '9', '13', 'My car got so stuck in a rut it required nine people pushing to get it out again.', 'JH', '1', 'キ', '', NULL, NULL),
('307', 'transport', '輸', '<img src=\"E8BCB8.png\" />', 'transport, car, meeting of butchers, umbrella, one, moon, month, flesh, part of the body, sword, sabre, saber', '16', '13', 'The car is a cattle-car, used to transport animals for the butcher´s meeting - a convention on new butchering techniques. Hear the screams of the animals as it pulls up in front of the convention hall, where the butchers are waiting with their knives out front.', '5', '2', 'ユ、シュ', '', NULL, NULL),
('308', 'metaphor', '喩・喻', '<img src=\"E596A9.png\" />', '', '12', '13', 'Metaphorically speaking, all the equipment in your mouth is basically just a meeting of butchers, designed to pulverize whatever meat you put in there.', 'JH', '', 'ユ', 'さと.す、 たと.える', NULL, NULL),
('309', 'in front', '前', '<img src=\"E5898D.png\" />', 'in front, horns, butcher, moon, month, flesh, part of the body, sword, sabre, saber', '9', '13', 'When I get horny my flesh sword sticks out in front of me.', '2', '5', 'ゼン', 'まえ、-まえ', NULL, NULL),
('31', 'gall bladder', '胆', '<img src=\"E88386.png\" />', 'gallbladder, moon, month, flesh, part of the body, nightbreak, sun, day, one, floor', '9', '2', 'The moon has a lot of gall sticking around after sunrise.', 'JH', '1', 'タン', 'きも', NULL, NULL),
('310', 'roast', '煎', '<img src=\"E7858E.png\" />', 'roast, in front, horns, butcher, moon, month, flesh, part of the body, sword, sabre, saber, oven-fire, barbecue', '13', '13', 'In many asian restaurants, meat is roasted right in front of you over flames.', 'JH', '', 'セン', 'せん.じる、い.る、に.る', NULL, NULL),
('311', 'each', '各', '<img src=\"E59084.png\" />', 'each, walking legs, mouth', '6', '13', 'Son, I´ve never told you this but each woman has a second mouth between their fiiiiiine walking legs.', '4', '2', 'カク', 'おのおの', NULL, NULL),
('312', 'status', '格', '<img src=\"E6A0BC.png\" />', 'status, tree, wood, each, walking legs, mouth', '10', '13', 'Ranger! I want you to go check the status of each tree. \"Errr, Each tree sir?\" replies the ranger looking out over the vast forest. \"That´s Right, I want the status of each tree! Move out!\".', '5', '3', 'カク、コウ、キャク、ゴウ', '', NULL, NULL),
('313', 'graft', '賂', '<img src=\"E8B382.png\" />', 'graft, shellfish, clam, oyster, eye, animal legs, eight, each, walking legs, mouth', '13', '14', 'It might sound simple to bribe someone, but then you have to graft the guy above him and the guy below him, and soon you´re just giving shells to each and everyone!', 'JH', '', 'ロ', 'まいな.い、まいな.う', NULL, NULL),
('314', 'abbreviation', '略', '<img src=\"E795A5.png\" />', 'abbreviation, rice field, brains, each, walking legs, mouth', '11', '13', 'There are so many abbreviations and acronyms nowadays that no brain can remember each of them. Mnemonic: ab-brain-each-ation.', '5', '2', 'リャク', 'ほぼ、おか.す、おさ.める、はかりごと、はか.る、はぶ.く、りゃく.す、りゃく.する', NULL, NULL),
('315', 'guest', '客', '<img src=\"E5AEA2.png\" />', 'guest, house, each, walking legs, mouth', '9', '13', 'Each person under my roof is treated as a guest.', '3', '3', 'キャク、カク', '', NULL, NULL),
('316', 'forehead', '額', '<img src=\"E9A18D.png\" />', 'forehead, guest, house, each, walking legs, mouth, head, page, one, ceiling, drop, shellfish, clam, oyster, eye, animal legs, eight', '18', '13', 'Sign the guestbook page with your forehead. (Picture a guestbook full of forehead prints like thumbprints).', '5', '2', 'ガク', 'ひたい', NULL, NULL),
('317', 'summer', '夏', '<img src=\"E5A48F.png\" />', 'summer, one, ceiling, drop, eye, walking legs', '10', '13', 'In SUMMER you are hot from the top of your head down to your walking legs.', '2', '4', 'カ、ガ、ゲ', 'なつ', NULL, NULL),
('318', 'dispose', '処', '<img src=\"E587A6.png\" />', 'dispose, walking legs, wind', '5', '13', 'The best way to dispose of a nasty bit of wind is to let it go and use those walking legs to dissapear. Nobody will ever know it was you.', '6', '3', 'ショ', 'ところ、-こ、お.る', NULL, NULL),
('319', 'twig', '条', '<img src=\"E69DA1.png\" />', 'twig, walking legs, tree, wood', '7', '13', 'They all say they have a TREE between their WALKING LEGS but most only have a TWIG.', '5', '1', 'ジョウ、チョウ、デキ', 'えだ、すじ', NULL, NULL),
('32', 'span', '亘', '<img src=\"E4BA98.png\" />', 'span, one, ceiling, sun, day, one, floor', '6', '2', 'The sun spans from horizon to horizon in a day.', 'Nam', '1', 'コウ、カン', 'わた.る、もと.める', NULL, NULL),
('320', 'fall', '落', '<img src=\"E890BD.png\" />', 'fall, flowers, water, water droplets, water pistol, each, walking legs, mouth', '12', '13', 'Water each flower or the petals will wither and fall.', '3', '3', 'ラク', 'お.ちる、お.ち、お.とす', NULL, NULL),
('321', 'superfluous', '冗', '<img src=\"E58697.png\" />', 'superfluous, crown, weathercock, wind', '4', '14', 'The king´s crown was blown off by the wind. \"Oh well,\" he said, \"it´s just a superfluous symbol.\".', 'JH', '1', 'ジョウ', '', NULL, NULL),
('322', 'Hades', '冥', '<img src=\"E586A5.png\" />', 'hades, crown, sun, day, six', '10', '14', 'The beast of hades one day will wear a crown, and the number of the beast is 666.', 'JH', '', 'メイ、ミョウ', 'くら.い', NULL, NULL),
('323', 'army', '軍', '<img src=\"E8BB8D.png\" />', 'army, chariot, crown, vehicle, car', '9', '14', 'British army cars are at the service of the crown.', '4', '2', 'グン', '', NULL, NULL),
('324', 'radiance', '輝', '<img src=\"E8BC9D.png\" />', 'radiance, ray, small, little, human legs, army, chariot, crown, vehicle, car', '15', '14', 'Rays of light emitted from Apollo´s chariot = radiance. Don´t put the sun into this kanji. The rays are coming from the chariot directly!', 'JH', '1', 'キ', 'かがや.く', NULL, NULL),
('325', 'carry', '運', '<img src=\"E9818B.png\" />', 'carry, army, chariot, crown, vehicle, car, road', '12', '14', 'Don’t confuse it with “take along” (287). In that one, there was a car so you could take along your friends once you found them on the road. In this one, there is an army chariot just to carry military supplies (sorry no room for you).', '3', '4', 'ウン', 'はこ.ぶ', NULL, NULL),
('326', 'crown', '冠', '<img src=\"E586A0.png\" />', 'crown, beginning, two, human legs, glue', '9', '14', 'Remember the SUPERFLUOUS CROWN that flew away in the WIND? Well now the king is saying \"i should have had the thing GLUED to my head from the BEGINNING\".', 'JH', '1', 'カン', 'かんむり', NULL, NULL),
('327', 'dream', '夢', '<img src=\"E5A4A2.png\" />', 'dream, flowers, eye, cross-eyed, net, crown, evening', '13', '14', 'Last night´s date with Miss Sweden was like a dream. She even laid flowers over my eyes to crown the perfect evening.', '5', '3', 'ム、ボウ', 'ゆめ、ゆめ.みる、くら.い', NULL, NULL),
('328', 'pit', '坑', '<img src=\"E59D91.png\" />', 'pit, soil, dirt, ground, whirlwind, top hat, wind', '7', '14', 'A whirlwind digs a hole in the ground throwing out lots of dirt until it ends up with a giant pit.', 'JH', '1', 'コウ', '', NULL, NULL),
('329', 'tall', '高', '<img src=\"E9AB98.png\" />', 'tall, top hat, mouth, alien, hood, mouth, mouth2', '10', '14', 'Two little aliens in a trenchcoat and top hat, trying to look TALL. The bottom one, in the glass helmet, is under the coat. The top one has his top hat pulled down in disguise, so all you can see is his mouth.', '2', '5', 'コウ', 'たか.い、たか、-だか、たか.まる、たか.める', NULL, NULL),
('33', 'concave', '凹', '<img src=\"E587B9.png\" />', 'concave', '5', '2', 'The letter \"U\" is concavely written.', 'JH', '1', 'オウ', 'くぼ.む、へこ.む、ぼこ', NULL, NULL),
('330', 'receive', '享', '<img src=\"E4BAAB.png\" />', 'receive, tall, top hat, mouth, children', '8', '14', 'In basketball however, tall children receive all the attention.', 'JH', '1', 'キョウ、コウ', 'う.ける', NULL, NULL),
