('840', 'promontory', '崎', '<img src=\"E5B48E.png\" />', 'promontory, mountain, strange, large, St. Bernard, can, street, nail, spike, mouth', '11', '24', 'This is “Cape Strange” from FRAME 153, only with mountain in place of soil. Interestingly, there is also 碕 which is made of the primitives stone and strange. The three kanjis 碕, 埼 and 崎 all have the same meanings and pronunciations. They have very little uses other than names, for which promontory is the clear winner with over 2300 uses in place and people names, while the other two kanjis account for less than 200 names.', 'JH', '1', 'キ', 'さき、さい、みさき', NULL, NULL),
('841', 'bluffs', '崖', '<img src=\"E5B496.png\" />', 'bluffs, mountain, cliff, ivy, square jewel, soil, dirt, ground, soil2, dirt2, ground2', '11', '24', 'Standing at the base of the bluffs I announce, \"I´m going to climb those ivy-covered cliffs, and then the mountain on top of them.\" My friends don´t believe me, \"He bluffs!\" they say.', 'JH', '', 'ガイ、ゲ、ギ', 'がけ、きし、はて', NULL, NULL),
('842', 'enter', '入', '<img src=\"E585A5.png\" />', 'enter', '2', '24', 'Pictograph, see book. * As a primitive, using the image of going through a door, even one that stands alone with the frame and no wall around, helps flesh out the primitive “enter”.', '1', '5', 'ニュウ、ジュ', 'い.る、-い.る、-い.り、い.れる、-い.れ、はい.る', NULL, NULL),
('843', 'crowded', '込', '<img src=\"E8BEBC.png\" />', 'crowded, enter, road', '5', '24', 'During a traffic jam it is impossible to get your car to enter the roadway as it is crowded with cars. Think of a grid lock so bad cars are litterally scraping up against each other like people on a Japanese train during rush hour.', 'JH', '3', '', 'こ.み、 -こ.み、 -こ.む、 こ.む、 こ.める', NULL, NULL),
