('957', 'equilibrium', '衡', '<img src=\"E8A1A1.png\" />', 'equilibrium, boulevard, going, bound up, rice field, brains, large, St. Bernard', '16', '25', 'To maintain the social equilibrium in a future dystopian society, the brains of citizens are bound up (hypnotized). The government is using mental wave emitting statues shaped like St. Bernard´s dogs put alongside the boulevards.', 'JH', '1', 'コウ', '', NULL, NULL),
('958', 'draft', '稿', '<img src=\"E7A8BF.png\" />', 'draft, wheat, cereal, tall, top hat, mouth, hood, mouth, mouth2', '15', '26', 'The first DRAFT of catcher in the rye was actually called \"catcher in the TALL WHEAT\"...good thing they changed it. I read it in 高校.', 'JH', '1', 'コウ', 'わら、したがき', NULL, NULL),
('959', 'earnings', '稼', '<img src=\"E7A8BC.png\" />', 'earnings, wheat, cereal, house, sow, pig', '15', '26', 'Your earnings allow you to bring home your daily bread (made of wheat, naturally).', 'JH', '1', 'カ', 'かせ.ぐ', NULL, NULL),
('96', 'village', '町', '<img src=\"E794BA.png\" />', 'village, rice field, brains, street, nail, spike', '7', '5', 'Actually this means town, like one that has lots of streets and is surrounded by all the rice fields.', '1', '4', 'チョウ', 'まち', NULL, NULL),
('960', 'extent', '程', '<img src=\"E7A88B.png\" />', 'extent, wheat, cereal, display, mouth, king, jewel, ball', '12', '26', 'The extent to which some people will go to create ´wheat displays´, or as some call them ´crop circles´, is truly amazing.', '5', '3', 'テイ', 'ほど、-ほど', NULL, NULL),
('961', 'tax', '税', '<img src=\"E7A88E.png\" />', 'tax, wheat, cereal, devil, horns, elder brother, teenager, mouth, human legs', '12', '26', 'Nobody likes the tax man, so here it is only fitting that the person who comes over to take some of your wheat is depicted here as a devil. Keep in mind that in feudal societies there was no kind of money to speak of, so taxes were paid by serfs in wheat to the devils who came over to keep them poor.', '5', '2', 'ゼイ', '', NULL, NULL),
('962', 'immature', '稚', '<img src=\"E7A89A.png\" />', 'immature, wheat, cereal, turkey', '13', '26', 'I can´t believe I brought you to the fanciest restaurant in town and you asked for turkey on wheat...how immature is that?!', 'JH', '1', 'チ、ジ', 'いとけない、おさない、おくて、おでる', NULL, NULL),
('963', 'harmony', '和', '<img src=\"E5928C.png\" />', 'harmony, wheat, cereal, mouth', '8', '26', 'The first step to harmony is having enough wheat to feed every mouth in the world. Once we are all fed it is easier to get a long in harmony.', '3', '3', 'ワ、オ、カ', 'やわ.らぐ、やわ.らげる、なご.む、なご.やか', NULL, NULL),
('964', 'shift', '移', '<img src=\"E7A7BB.png\" />', 'shift, wheat, cereal, many, evening, evening2', '11', '26', 'Picture the WHEAT field, filled with MANY, MANY stalks of WHEAT. Notice how they SHIFT like waves in the slightest breeze. When you hear SHIFT, just picture that scene.', '5', '2', 'イ', 'うつ.る、うつ.す', NULL, NULL),
('965', 'second', '秒', '<img src=\"E7A792.png\" />', 'second, wheat, cereal, few', '9', '26', 'An hourglass filled with wheat counts time. A few wheat seeds drop every second.', '3', '2', 'ビョウ', '', NULL, NULL),
('966', 'autumn', '秋', '<img src=\"E7A78B.png\" />', 'autumn, wheat, cereal, fire', '9', '26', 'In AUTUMN, the WHEAT looks the color of FIRE, meaning it´s time to harvest it.', '2', '4', 'シュウ', 'あき、とき', NULL, NULL),
('967', 'distress', '愁', '<img src=\"E68481.png\" />', 'distress, autumn, wheat, cereal, fire, heart', '13', '26', 'In AUTUMN, the farmer´s HEART is in DISTRESS as to if he has enough crops. Even better, the farmer will experience great DISTRESS in his HEART if his WHEAT catches FIRE!', 'JH', '1', 'シュウ', 'うれ.える、うれ.い', NULL, NULL),
('968', 'private', '私', '<img src=\"E7A781.png\" />', 'private, wheat, cereal, elbow', '7', '26', 'Warning sign: \"Private wheat, trespassers will be elbowed\".', '6', '4', 'シ', 'わたくし、わたし', NULL, NULL),
('969', 'regularity', '秩', '<img src=\"E7A7A9.png\" />', 'regularity, wheat, cereal, lose, drop, husband', '10', '26', 'Think of REGULARITY in terms of bowel movements. Enough WHEAT in your diet will help your DROPS with improved REGULARITY.', 'JH', '1', 'チツ', '', NULL, NULL),
('97', 'can', '可', '<img src=\"E58FAF.png\" />', 'can, mouth, street, street, nail, spike', '5', '5', 'A mouth on the street asking for things: \"Can I get some help?! Can I get directions, Can I have some money? Can you please speak English?!\".', '5', '', 'カ、コク', '-べ.き', NULL, NULL),
('970', 'secret', '秘', '<img src=\"E7A798.png\" />', 'secret, wheat, cereal, invariably, heart, drop', '10', '26', 'The prize at the bottom of a cereal box is invariably a secret decoder ring.', '6', '1', 'ヒ', 'ひ.める、ひそ.か、かく.す', NULL, NULL),
('971', 'appellation', '称', '<img src=\"E7A7B0.png\" />', 'appellation, wheat, cereal, hammock, reclining, lying down, small, little', '10', '26', 'Taking appellation to mean the act of naming, we have the little baby superman reclining in the space craft that landed in a wheat field. Mr. and Mrs. Kent look down and decide to call him Clark. (I also thought of Jesus but he was born in a barn full of hay not wheat).', 'JH', '1', 'ショウ', 'たた.える、とな.える、あ.げる、かな.う、はか.り、はか.る、ほめ.る', NULL, NULL),
('972', 'profit', '利', '<img src=\"E588A9.png\" />', 'profit, wheat, cereal, sword, sabre, saber', '7', '26', 'In the middle ages there where only 2 ways for peasantry to make a profit. one by being a farmer, 2 to be a mercenary and live by the way of the sword.', '4', '3', 'リ', 'き.く', NULL, NULL),
('973', 'pear tree', '梨', '<img src=\"E6A2A8.png\" />', 'pear tree, profit, wheat, cereal, sword, sabre, saber, tree, wood', '11', '26', 'The Japanese pear tree is the most profitable in the world, because it produces its fruit in pairs [sorry for the awful pun].', 'JH', '1', 'リ', 'なし', NULL, NULL),
('974', 'harvest', '穫', '<img src=\"E7A9AB.png\" />', 'harvest, wheat, cereal, radio caroline, flowers, vessels, turkey, crotch', '18', '26', 'The harvest of genetically modified crops is taken onboard the Greenpeace vessel (see the flower vessel in safeguard (#700)).', 'JH', '1', 'カク', '', NULL, NULL),
('975', 'ear of a plant', '穂', '<img src=\"E7A982.png\" />', 'ear (of a plant), wheat, cereal, favour, favor, ten, needle, rice field, brains, heart', '15', '26', 'The pilgrims only had wheat, so they asked the Indians to do them a favor and trade them for some ears of corn.', 'JH', '1', 'スイ', 'ほ', NULL, NULL),
('976', 'rice plant', '稲', '<img src=\"E7A8B2.png\" />', 'rice plant, wheat, cereal, claw, vulture, old days, olden times, stick, sun, day', '14', '26', 'The rice plant is common in Japan because all the wheat was eaten by vultures in the olden times.', 'JH', '1', 'トウ、テ', 'いね、いな-', NULL, NULL),
('977', 'incense', '香', '<img src=\"E9A699.png\" />', 'incense, wheat, cereal, sun, day', '9', '26', 'If you focus the suns though a magnifying glass on to the bottom of a stalk of wheat it will start to smoulder and burn like a stick of incense. The weird thing is that it burns from the bottom upwards, hanging in the air as if my magic. Try it and see!', 'JH', '2', 'コウ、キョウ', 'か、かお.り、かお.る', NULL, NULL),
('978', 'seasons', '季', '<img src=\"E5ADA3.png\" />', 'seasons, wheat, cereal, child', '8', '26', 'There´s a season for planting wheat and there´s mating season for having children.', '4', '2', 'キ', '', NULL, NULL),
('979', 'committee', '委', '<img src=\"E5A794.png\" />', 'committee, wheat, cereal, woman', '8', '26', 'Female WHEAT farmers decide to create a COMMITTEE, which they fittingly name “The WHEAT WOMEN COMMITTEE.”.', '3', '2', 'イ', 'ゆだ.ねる', NULL, NULL),
('98', 'place on the head', '頂', '<img src=\"E9A082.png\" />', 'place on the head, street, nail, spike, head, page, one, ceiling, drop, shellfish, clam, oyster, eye, animal legs, eight', '11', '5', 'If I put a street sign on my head what do I get ? A place on the head !', '6', '3', 'チョウ', 'いただ.く、いただき', NULL, NULL),
('980', 'excel', '秀', '<img src=\"E7A780.png\" />', 'excel, wheat, cereal, fist, from', '7', '26', 'You spend three hours putting all of your wheat sale transaction records into Microsoft Excel, when suddenly it crashes, so you put your fist through the monitor.', 'JH', '1', 'シュウ', 'ひい.でる', NULL, NULL),
('981', 'transparent', '透', '<img src=\"E9808F.png\" />', 'transparent, excel, wheat, cereal, fist, from, road', '10', '26', 'If you excel in the Mario Kart road, your movements are saved and you can race against yourself as a transparent racer. http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Xe8CkcrL-k4.', 'JH', '1', 'トウ', 'す.く、す.かす、す.ける、とう.る、とう.す', NULL, NULL),
('982', 'entice', '誘', '<img src=\"E8AA98.png\" />', 'entice, say, words, keitai, mouth, excel, wheat, cereal, fist, from', '14', '26', 'Think of the smooth talker who EXCELS at using WORDS to entice women (including married women if it makes it easier to remember).', 'JH', '1', 'ユウ、イウ', 'さそ.う、いざな.う', NULL, NULL),
('983', 'training', '稽', '<img src=\"E7A8BD.png\" />', 'training, wheat, cereal, understandably, chihuahua with one human leg, delicious, spoon, sitting on the ground, sun, day', '15', '26', 'After a hard day of training, wheat is understandably delicious.', 'JH', '', 'ケイ', 'かんが.える、とど.める', NULL, NULL),
('984', 'cereals', '穀', '<img src=\"E7A980.png\" />', 'cereals, samurai, crown, wheat, cereal, cruise missile, missile, wind, crotch', '14', '26', 'There are different cereals in different parts of the world. Japan has samurai cereal. Great Britain has Crowned Wheat ... the United States and Russia have Missile cereals.', '6', '1', 'コク', '', NULL, NULL),
('985', 'germ', '菌', '<img src=\"E88F8C.png\" />', 'germ, flowers, pent in, wheat, cereal', '11', '26', 'Can also mean bacteria.....imagine the wheat pent in your fridge growing to the point where they resemble flowers.......I actually had something similar happen to onions...they grew footlong legs after about 2 or 3 years......OR just think of that Cowboy Bebop episode with the lobster in the fridge... :-).', 'JH', '1', 'キン', '', NULL, NULL),
('986', 'numb', '萎', '<img src=\"E8908E.png\" />', 'numb, flowers, committee, wheat, cereal, woman', '11', '26', 'Oh, the committee´s in for a surprise: I put some nightshades into their drinks. They´ll be numb for sure, probably worse.', 'JH', '', 'イ', 'な、しお.れる、しな.びる、しぼ.む、な.える', NULL, NULL),
('987', 'rice', '米', '<img src=\"E7B1B3.png\" />', 'rice', '6', '26', 'Stroke order: I like to think of the first two strokes as “chop sticks” with which one eats the rice. The rest then is the “tree” meaning “plant” in this contexct. also: USA.', '2', '3', 'ベイ、マイ、メエトル', 'こめ、よね', NULL, NULL),
('988', 'flour', '粉', '<img src=\"E7B289.png\" />', 'flour, rice, part, eight, sword, dagger', '10', '26', 'Parts of parts of parts of parts of rice... is flour. (Image: geishas patting their face with RICE flour to make it white. Not wheat flour...).', '4', '2', 'フン、デシメートル', 'こ、こな', NULL, NULL),
('989', 'sticky', '粘', '<img src=\"E7B298.png\" />', 'sticky, rice, fortune-telling, magic wand, augury, mouth', '11', '26', 'This is another way of fortune telling -- throw sticky rice against the wall, and look for the message in whatever sticks.', 'JH', '1', 'ネン', 'ねば.る', NULL, NULL),
('99', 'child', '子', '<img src=\"E5AD90.png\" />', 'child', '3', '6', 'A child who is ten will still ask for his ma (top looks a bit like katakana ma).', '1', '5', 'シ、ス、ツ', 'こ、-こ、ね', NULL, NULL),
('990', 'grains', '粒', '<img src=\"E7B292.png\" />', 'grains, rice, vase, stand up', '11', '26', 'A sage is using rice to fill up a vase, but as an exercise in patience, he´s doing it grain by grain.', 'JH', '2', 'リュウ', 'つぶ', NULL, NULL),
('991', 'cosmetics', '粧', '<img src=\"E7B2A7.png\" />', 'cosmetics, rice, shire, cave, soil, dirt, ground', '12', '26', 'Condy Rice is actually white, but she uses special cosmetics made from dirt she found in a cave to appear black - it´s better for the political situation.', 'JH', '', 'ショウ', '', NULL, NULL),
('992', 'astray', '迷', '<img src=\"E8BFB7.png\" />', 'astray, rice, road', '9', '26', 'The road that the USA is heading down is, well... let´s just say that they´re astray...', '5', '3', 'メイ', 'まよ.う', NULL, NULL),
('993', 'chic', '粋', '<img src=\"E7B28B.png\" />', 'chic, rice, ninety, nine, baseball, ten, needle', '10', '26', 'In extremely chic restaurants, you have to pay 90 bucks for a bowl of rice.', 'JH', '1', 'スイ', 'いき', NULL, NULL),
('994', 'riddle', '謎', '<img src=\"E8AC8E.png\" />', 'riddle, say, words, keitai, mouth, astray, rice, road', '16', '26', 'Words meant to lead you astray are those of a riddle.', 'JH', '', 'メイ、ベイ', 'なぞ', NULL, NULL),
('995', 'provisions', '糧', '<img src=\"E7B3A7.png\" />', 'provisions, rice, quantity, nightbreak, sun, day, one, floor, computer', '18', '26', 'Imagine Japanese army provisions like obentou boxes, always containing the same quantity of rice. (thanks darg_sama, emphasizing quantity and the nuance of food \"rations\", \"food supply\": the kanji also appears in \"military provisions\" and \"army rice\").', 'JH', '1', 'リョウ、ロウ', 'かて', NULL, NULL),
('996', 'chrysanthemum', '菊', '<img src=\"E88F8A.png\" />', 'chrysanthemum, flowers, rice cooker, bound up, rice', '11', '26', 'Chrysanthemum flower consists of many tiny petals, just like many rice grains bound up together.', 'JH', '1', 'キク', '', NULL, NULL),
('997', 'core', '奥', '<img src=\"E5A5A5.png\" />', 'core, drop, pent in, rice, large, St. Bernard', '12', '26', 'In the core of a nuclear reactor, scientists have discovered a way to get power from rice, by penting it in under high pressure. It´s very dangerous, so they´ve trained a st. bernard dog to run things, he´s adding more drops of rice as necessary.', 'JH', '2', 'オウ、オク', 'おく.まる、くま', NULL, NULL),
('998', 'number', '数', '<img src=\"E695B0.png\" />', 'number, rice, woman, taskmaster', '13', '26', 'Young taskmaster is learning numbers by watching women haul sacks of rice past him. \"One... two... four! No, wrong! Go back, go back!\".', '2', '3', 'スウ、ス、サク、ソク、シュ', 'かず、かぞ.える、しばしば、せ.める、わずらわ.しい', NULL, NULL),
('999', 'watchtower', '楼', '<img src=\"E6A5BC.png\" />', 'watchtower, tree, wood, rice, woman', '13', '26', 'The young taskmaster (see number (#929)) uses a tree as a watchtower to get a better view of his rice-carrying women. \"I can seeeee you! One! Two! Three!\".', 'JH', '1', 'ロウ', 'たかどの', NULL, NULL);
